M T H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVgQXbERtd5HF9rqLJE0f90rRoOWDjkZPbLG23FClFBq0z4H6hvnw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I forgot to take photos when I visited there for the first time because I was too excited to meet my friends, but the drinks and food were amazing. I ended up coming back within two weeks because I loved it so much. The whole menu is unique, and as a farm-to-table spot, their veggies and meats are incredibly flavorful. I don’t usually drink cocktails, but their gin \u0026 tonic was perfectly balanced with bitterness, sweetness, and aroma. The Old Fashioned was also great with their rich, flavorful whiskey. It’s kid- and dog-friendly, with plenty of parking. I’ll definitely be back to try more.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2J-IP9zH5ogGMPB9Nir4D0G0m941BZ18dL5_-2lFZymkDMBAILPZSURR4ycCDnH1Ib56X_qAsfZhvkRQYKe-gy2NLUrlOntMLKNKAT6jiG7j1oXBVWi2_exUqFY6hmM25i23oBb8T9zvk=k-no"],"When":"2025-11-17"},{"Name":"Jill Beringer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWj4zPXtIF53ghqHgTqaEN67KNzrsjeDRPVddk5IFkGbguCLVEj=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I grew up in this area and it’s really exciting to come home to visit and experience this sort of dining in lil ol kenmore! Everything we tried was so yummy, the porchetta roast was perfect for sharing, especially paired with a gin cocktail! Can’t wait to come back and eat again, we want to try the whole winter menu","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3yorRYSEC0Rp3OBN8dDDcF0--i2fDI1bFFojWMaonus4Oh-Y0JLjQFlQ_A3zfCJMYp6uwjV1IME8QZTAv71n_mMZScceDxF7dU1P1Dr4Mg1XogiPClqVjqh9L3OLEbHl8H2wRtCNeEeZ8=k-no"],"When":"2025-12-7"},{"Name":"Ofoda Inalej","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVUMUqbzeGgtV1nq6Z3_TlC4V1Xu644lO8DAC-Fm__gciTMTdQo7Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Meet with a colleague and split the porchetta. Everything was tasty. Would have been awesome had skin been more cracklin like, salad needed like another textual component like duqqa or nuts, maybe even a cheese. Regardless Everything was delicious.\nHighly recommend","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2QlCRaYQb4T1Rba5DKRMyg-tGbRU1c4f0VPZJk_ZyNRpoMpWsGnvVnU1hpkPiZmuKL7BLU-cchQNuYfgG6QjeTYNLbCOnDdB7B4ZdTFjghwiyH9NMZByCNOIYNDT48eggLh0kIK7edY8oo=k-no"],"When":"2026-1-14"},{"Name":"Blair Anderson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVczOVXow6lTv0bMeMJFpe89F20ii4Lc9hgvzYsZrQs3_N1HzyL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"De La Soil is crazy. Part fine dining, Part fast casual.\n\nYou order at the bar, grab your number, the food comes 5 minutes later.\n\nWhen the food comes it looks straight from a michelin star kitchen. Nice plating, bright colors, good portion size.\n\nEvery dish was great. Not very often food inspires me to write long reviews but these guys are just great.\n\nother cool things:\n- i watched the chef go to the garden for herbs.\n- they have kids toys, kids menu\n- outdoor and indoor seating\n- connected to distillery\n\ndefinitely coming back.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn14FaLhLhkvwaYRqx1rp1hge1h52Q0c8rgydG6mxLRRskhOv5ENqL5jl8YDSlXOG_xMttrsQWKQlutPI5tqI_75tkLz7xUjVBZd4-RzpHFzKkMeWhaNy4ww1gYH24iyU7Uc-vZz7Kz5lrW0=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn06c3OZYU88sz_mkoftPzbnU_EFQdOF5ort2C1H0KVrLueqED7rt0xfYsQKEh8kWCWLCp2mTvIL1Lwbjb_XjL_eO6ElHj-KKnf-mmtxSyW4iiUUPOc9EatNAzkvf6opFhErqmm3ibxzrPg=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3u3Vx1WYEdMUvWcqeo7EZKqHHLusCG-WZ6vK3i3iCoTwkcZixZdBBJGUSokyQB1wlRi-9de6jQz7TntvlqnPfdRF1hLnLURT7SPKaV8geHntagT3c58t-cgSSmdUOd68eko0zwonN2IWwE=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2eSyuf9t7gg5kLDwxfybgBpeO71iOWp-tOW4H6DWITylH-XEByErM2R9O5j2LVv07Byh2blt7aA_7zV6oCHZumVIR-u9FdWHnr2TEJ6KOxmtLTem-0XvPcIqjEnN4fDJiaRtjhgs-vdLZ0=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com