ered the baked French toast and vegan tofu scramble. Both were well prepared and we enjoyed the food a lot. Place is on the expensive side compared to other places but then food and ambiance compensated for it.\n\nI liked the place and will visit again.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2Yb8sy9_pu7LtySbZiwJhlyIW9aAC0ORV1lYMbRJkDMqNSmsV3UcAFAeOQZU8xYTeAifMUYmBw9KKp5lcI0fXJ4FDhFEAVrUDv4aPO6PeRj9pfmRD4AdhU7qk6WwUO7oboqrtO3wqsb058=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3p73boo-EYAVNGPAucPO-Lxx-04ymgc3IGEJUAkLNbRmQvrj9-NnrCZFcY_RMo1nrz7u0uhI6i5d58bbpjti4UARhABVLyLdoDpgZFrKJyxj9UekatWj-fpu4uk0HiyvPBda-Ci7R8D6cy=k-no"],"When":"2026-1-26"},{"Name":"Epic Chefs","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW25paR4awhSgRUzmyapXRyX3rPZgdUmN-eJIhwjJKXGetu2OOm=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"You HAVE to get the shortrib hash. 9.5 /10.  Delicious. Crispy potatoes, juicy and flavorful meat, great aioli...all around, a real treat!  The wife said this Avocado Toast was the best she's had. Great bread, fresh avocado... perfect.\n\nI also had the Gingerbread latte. I consider myself something of an afficionado, since I make 20 dozen Gingerbread cookies every year.  This was perfect. Not too heavy, lots of flavor and  the perfect foam on top.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1ufiNKUr6eGJ6vVYAd8gqgDkf3ktWAGKY3_gltya2D9DUhD419RvdHjy2Pq6U5nyZV5PLf45ayHU4zf5ulM3dJWer-fT1FIiK-9EiL4DFMGPHpTgb2HCNj3NdgGv5aULto9sOcnctgyoM=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2KSBKQVEeAzZ7Tm1QmldJejOZ_2teNy1TTcF_J5dIFZpWdDqIs2o8pv_5Ry8I77TixLPwqllxwq7tlaqws5vT2wcAuN_FWpKsmp5P_qnfaI2AI5hwg8EGhP0fiSLo4BKwg1g5uNM2W4KyD=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3LjG_pA9jMeAKGKz9cv5rxNKNE3RSLGKWaY0nl61c08Ez2bwxRvNuFJJiGNmPvCi4d4AMksKVF0TxtzTBUInZoHjVZzBq9VgrLXHzMp2uArFmLSc9rwrOZfT-lXqsYGM0BevALABggav9h=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1CpHZXCfK5B4ohUJsq2x6e7