,"enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Lunch reservations recommended","enabled":true},{"name":"Dinner reservations recommended","enabled":true},{"name":"Accepts reservations","enabled":true},{"name":"Usually a wait","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]},{"id":"children","name":"Children","options":[{"name":"Good for kids","enabled":true},{"name":"Has changing table(s)","enabled":true},{"name":"High chairs","enabled":true},{"name":"Kids' menu","enabled":true}]},{"id":"parking","name":"Parking","options":[{"name":"Free parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Free street parking","enabled":true},{"name":"Valet parking","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"K Z","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKpf8qiEHTxJmYtSUb5O3ffjTsAJRd7yTE9wB0KQImU-iovBQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"So excited to finally try this place! I get why they are highly rated. The food and service here is excellent. We wandered in on a random Thursday during lunch hour and the place was packed! however, we did snack two seats at a high top table. Our server was Sara and she was so attentive and kind. She gave us recs on what she liked the most here and made sure we got the 25% WA resident discount. We ordered the broccoli, basket fries, mediterranean vegan pasta, and smoked gouda cream chicken. The food was out quick and piping hot. Everything was fresh and made to order. One of the managers stopped by a couple times to check in on us and asked us how we liked everything. This service is unmatched! It was also a belated birthday celebration so they celebrated by giving us a free dessert. To be noted - they have plenty of vegan options here and are willing to substitute as well. This quickly became one of my favorite spots to eat and I can't wait to be back! Thanks to Sara and the managers at Von's for a lovely experience!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3I5U2sKtRsxD8CNVT8Sf6iNntRJPkGCCFO5MUCCn9iFR6vFNYwniGZ27gOK1Z7JC3gXkwH12P2emeLKGt35I4y_cw5Uv2lMbpsilqs2p-xsQzFjBM_R7hs0uerxAowoffI2emTDSES2msz=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3dGXDbuSwIrjuUzuzIcoVBokKJOCnOb4EJs9t1HGo40kX8DJ0xDc42juTEHfePNn60lJb-2ODJUA8JON0nBzoh7D5iDvNWSik6Wyq8Ipu2MpFWoV0pYoaIE8CGEfXdTvQErBVIRXqgNMs=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0nNe6DMhMq8mRpRIFSNAHle3NCCz0ABeVTj0p4de_-4GrzWYa1zr-19wCtvFTV_aUyziTxixf57G43PnzVuGAI_9a9NS1FtYI0UP4wY05SNOIz8LSiMonlK-KO1FthVIHPfRp8t1MAB30Y=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1i3bkv2bDFxTMaP_xSLZIgTCJ7NU_kLpnnKEUy1E9iTtZG2xrg_9tmZrkF59LwToQ6M6mH9gHy3qeUpsWSuhsFqVFhltbxs6Q79QCJHn-7du_SqNd_z6w5cQqoiRON_ddTAoEnybjFvC_M=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3Z7M5kihP-Xp-xuR4wFS1mYU0yHTseO_N0xKXoE0PWtQvFbRdHlO_w3rtBtvUszvgTzBaPWMGrkONYZi1C7IPoYaGkKAhSzkp4xrGZzwHvW_r35GhRmo_jor77WdIynJW_gjXMPBdvT4iQ=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0PhQ95MtkTot41egO-mOe9CitVrQg9RHth3klBJA_1EsZXqsK3qoBXb7Zgqr57trSyHhMVBP_K3GN0hhsl-UvqpQz-fxwtMPGoXG-xgUVU8TwJRJL_mQILWGlEVzR8cDZElXI3bxBgY2Yc=k-no"],"When":"2025-12-13"},{"Name":"Mr. T-Bone","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVSuUVL6z8O5kGrJ20pewuJ2wv8hO2pbpzY9Ak_Stqhf0fBFnu1=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Von’s 1000 Spirits — Sourdough Done Right, Even for a Franchise\n\nRating: ★★★★★ (5/5)\n\nAfter an afternoon at Château Ste. Michelle, we stopped by Von’s 1000 Spirits expecting something casual and convenient. What we found instead was a sourdough-driven kitchen that genuinely impressed me — enough to earn a rare five-star rating, especially for a restaurant with multiple locations. This visit exceeded expectations in both execution and flavor.\n\nAmbiance – 4.5/5\nVon’s strikes a lively yet relaxed balance — energetic without feeling chaotic. The open kitchen and warm lighting give it a rustic, modern feel, ideal for unwinding after wine tasting. It feels social and approachable, yet still polished enough for a proper sit-down meal.\n\nAuthenticity – 4.5/5\nWhat sets Von’s apart is its dedication to sourdough — not as a gimmick, but as a defining technique. Both the pizza and pasta showcase fermentation depth and texture that go beyond standard Italian-American fare. There’s a craftsmanship here that feels intentional rather than mass-produced.\n\nFlavor – 5/5\nThe sourdough pizza was a standout — airy yet structured, with a subtle tang that elevated every topping. The crust had proper blistering and chew, reminiscent of artisan pizzerias rather than chain-style execution.\n\nEqually impressive was the sourdough pasta. The fermentation added complexity and body to the dish, creating a depth that’s rare in casual dining settings. It’s not often that pasta surprises me, but this one did.\n\nService – 5/5\nOur server was attentive, knowledgeable, and genuinely welcoming. Timing was smooth, and her recommendations for drinks were spot on for my wife and helpful, and the overall hospitality felt sincere rather than transactional.\n\nCost – 5/5\nFor the quality of ingredients and execution, the pricing felt extremely fair. Considering the craftsmanship behind their sourdough program, the value is exceptional.\n\nFinal Thoughts\nVon’s 1000 Spirits proves that a restaurant with multiple locations can still deliver personality and precision. It’s rare that I award five stars to a franchise-style establishment, but this one earned it through thoughtful technique, excellent flavor, and polished service. I will absolutely be returning.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0vx632OcSUxyQlYHUnzYGFyO20BDuKYbFfmhul2APEkbrQruSbRzaCQove0Q2apZzMh0JomCAz1VdzbSh16XrAa7RvrcaKKCIzhCHYzjckRq9lynA3t4tIzaHOE-7InWkDBQVTrWcdfTD-=k-no","https://lh3.googleuser