ass-cs/ANxoTn3l36cLtaEIn_qqabriAxR-kKImKK9XLo2DqnhDsEj6npKPWAJC-MN9w7bUCvFqZc_DbujvB_RzrzzHqu1E_eivwdfvVz8px9ldi5XqU9C0PDJw8KFHTmHKHyrTwdQRBaBRESj_Mt4QPwHT=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0KJ4nhRdHFPgriE5jDqx9h1VhVqETVCAV8hbMh2y_O7CeQSdVP4oupt46rBrniV-D_e0WoyvhlmvWavdOdznwn6wSPeh-rz4WnU4wB3tBcwkIAIinvc9eS7wndgRmbt7AoYL7wlEC4vzHy=k-no"],"When":"2026-2-25"},{"Name":"808TryWaitTryWait","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWNgP5HPRI9CNY6JJf57AyCDFiT9Xr0qJotBVF8sRPbq5lGnAoy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Visited back in May of 2025.\n\nPARKING: Valet park, but we got there on a Sunday when it opened (11:30 AM) and the valet person wasn't there, so we just self-parked. Stall spaces are limited, so perhaps that's why the valet service.\n\nSERVICE: Super amazing, as was the Seattle location. Our server Angel - very amazing server. Having great service makes everything taste way better.\n\nMENU: Vegan and Veg-friendly dishes, a plus! Pizzas are crafted from sourdough and fired in a wood-oven, chewy pizza dough with crispy crusts and special cheeses (none of that industrial stuff), with fresh herbs. Fries are all hand-cut real stuff, not that frozen stuff. The hummus and eggplant appetizer was supremely and ridiculously delicious! Smash Burger was juicy. Bang Bang Chicken was mind-altering, according to the son.\n\nCOCKTAILS: All crafted with fresh juices and mixes, the finest spirits. My Classic Margarita came with a black lava salted rim, whoa! Flavors are all spot-on. Nothing industrial, nothing poured out of a plastic bottle from wholesale places, everything is scratch, and it shows.\n\nAs in my previous review of Von's 1000 Spirits in Seattle, the vodka is so smooth, it's amazing, forget Tito's, forget Chopin, forget Gray Goose, forget Hangar One - go straight to Northwest Spirits next door and buy yourselves the best vodka (distilled 6-times like Tito's but without the bite).\n\nPIZZAS: You have to try t