t.com/a-/ALV-UjWTYPlAQ91cH7b0bwrFh7QF5aj_EgWhQHIAvIEUBoreN8mfQ_63fQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently had the pleasure of eating at Ta Joia in Bothell for lunch, and it was a truly delightful experience. This small, vibrant restaurant is full of charm—with its bright colors, cozy atmosphere, and beautiful indoor plants that instantly caught my eye. As a big plant lover, I really appreciated the greenery that added a refreshing and calming touch to the space. The restaurant is clean, well-lit, and has a welcoming, lively vibe that makes you feel right at home.\n\nWe ordered the Grilled Shrimp Bowl and the Spicy Chicken Bowl, and both dishes were outstanding. The portion sizes were generous, and everything was cooked to perfection. The shrimp tasted fresh and paired wonderfully with the rice and the standout cilantro sauce—it was absolutely amazing. The spicy chicken was grilled beautifully, with a slight crisp on the outside while still juicy and tender on the inside. The spice level was just right, enhancing the flavors without being overpowering.\n\nOverall, the food was not only delicious but also comforting—like a really good home-cooked meal that satisfies both your hunger and your soul. I left feeling happy, full, and already looking forward to my next visit. There are more dishes I can’t wait to try!\n\nTa Joia is a gem, and I highly recommend it to anyone looking for flavorful food in a cheerful and inviting setting.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3Lhi9pSOz53QQttEU_9U86QBeYgKUUGxGKTqoVv3-i7MEGEIOsHiEe7MTrudn-6cbwS3p26a1kDgpeOp7Z7rSv8L_O4AZFtaYsECb82cTjPjFFfmk6mbFMUCC9cgw_8l377ho=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1y44yebo6vQsESgW0bUUG6NSK0zQzUufCNidk7asAPPGmnsznySZ7MiVadb5Sim9qYwbtQLLm40xUHJpBffLgkku1IFxIYazEtzACsZ31hh6q6X449Zx8nDH1ONYBYVfXa6H61bQ=k-no"],"When":"2025-5-17"},{"Name":"Andrew Do","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW0YyEBGMZqGmr-GrOIFVxsLCgpT8ZyexFkkX58rEgstscmcv4zmg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have been coming here since they opened! The spicy chicken option for either thigh or breast are my wife and I’s favorite. All of the flavors explode in your mouth with deep Asian seasoning and a mix of Latin pico de gallo with a creamy side of cilantro lime sauce. Absolutely delicious, I highly recommend this place if you want an elevated teriyaki style meal made with love, and always presented beautifully.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tiffany Beddoe","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVgdB-3q6ihvlubpPYbroMk2RDqh-ctncYTtC3A5xDipeVnfoEo4A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"You can’t go wrong with any option on the menu! Delicious, fresh, homemade and you will be rewarded chatting with the lovely staff too. They always make everyone feel so welcome. Great energy and get the extra cilantro sauce and pico. Crispy Chicken Bowl is my favorite. Yum!","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
