ting":5,"Description":"I'll give it to you that this place is pretty expensive, but the quality of food is incredibly high and the service is fantastic. So maybe you want to splurge a little more, but I have to say the food is fantastic. Their double Smashburger is definitely one of the best I've had in months, if not years.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2M_EiX1NpgCBZvcV6cPS4PobmlIFSZfmN--3elkg-RJe7NzA8o6dOyy-kW_4TtrWKcyBX5yetntGzNEUg85IfcVZ1lgAujkglfAyNlPQn9pn2xb5JYSk03my9Tcy34pv8utLHD-CEbvd8=k-no"],"When":"2026-1-23"},{"Name":"emily p","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLS_xr4oAKS4EuEBjazt_7nGZiPE9-Wfg-lfmvzYEE55lkHZw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Another visit to Beardslee Public House and another exceptional experience. Time and time again, the chefs, staff, and bartenders perform. They make deliciously beautiful food from scratch and you can really tell. This visit I went with a friend to celebrate a bit achievement. I ordered the fried chicken sandwich with fries. Wow! It wasn’t one bit greasy, so crunchy and fresh, and the chipotle sauce was outstanding. As always, the “fry sauce” and ranch were the correct dipping sauces for the fries. My friend ordered the lemon chicken and mashed potatoes and loved it. My friend’s father had a bit of a complicated order but the kitchen delivered and he enjoyed his burger. We also really enjoyed the mules (I ordered a regular one and my friend’s father got the peach and really liked it). If we didn’t have to drive we definitely would’ve had another round. But we saved it for next time. I’m slowly eating my way through the menu and I haven’t been disappointed yet. Also, the happy hour menu has wonderful food \u0026 drink options!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn08F7dhZ6WV5O-WN66w9NeZr7nzKDEqCBTqQ0AvtDEOMVpuzGRiLOg5VZiWMCSKcNClP530cThvETlBE71tv4MybdmnsusAdarv838it6VyZuwqJEqViHhHJYO-GgdAWsLCAJAS=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3yJpWq-1IU0wiQmd_u92ugp2jz5GFLaJ1cN5MpAeyowAB7K6Dib3MjMH-VOyGtSKlR5ykB0TDrHGvZUP3FSZPrtHR56qtTaCPtbPGS5dltKUgof9n380rQ5fzeuoK4eQls9ZtDvQ=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1MRHueoDkANPIfob_AI95Ocojl51el5tAgM6V6_AjywurKhkd7TQrgXCCFqNXM5r-Xsi-ODfc01Z07PrPvEPpOyk0IswEKVeSBFWHEq0OJLoLjgWrO09gXXo2qF0I2eVgdhUs=k-no"],"When":"2025-6-9"},{"Name":"Jeff","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX8RExAnsR4eOHNpbrcYM0FfXL99KtvO67tY_ciuOWL3W0wwVU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Solid upscale casual bar and grill with an abundance of drink options including a couple of non-alcoholic beer options that are *thankfully* not O’Doul’s.  Happy hour until 6, a large screen tuned to sports, attentive courteous staff, and a solid menu make for a great dining experience.  Burger options are a little more expensive but include choices that are not standard pub fare like a french onion dip smash burger.  A mix of upscale and casual with a broad menu to fit most, they pleasantly accommodate larger groups, making Beardslee Public House a great choice if you’re considering where to go for a special occasion.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn14cAraNKGPZ6W8tTMbv_aIEXHV3TfV_K31iokznOFtxtf_tB7IZbGfuMbttTxQR6VydCzBQkrApLDkk3bbFT-ZkBIoYrIBBEjpk8JGq1T7K4-mXzcVsitBMhS2s-7ny-efarufsUnpXFDR=k-no"],"When":"2025-10-29"},{"Name":"Eric Thoni","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUK_1NpTE1A7AaNzkv06UWSJ3PGGceljH2F5DyFO5VPHbw7Kj7Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the best smash burgies I’ve had in a long while. The beers were great, service was exceptional and laid back atmosphere. Just walked in because my hotel was across the street but I was blown away.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3tAlf-3KT8EeCwEl74bK87-lE3Qtl4mNiNJuZ_Pp50yjUm7ttF94yyUBb-e658Tjth92AF_d9ojrDrAp4VuSVPC3Nn2KBH3sjXtNN7d-Hl4-eYDjFcVp5YVN5rT2M_X_1uCs_zvy