]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Checks","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]},{"id":"parking","name":"Parking","options":[{"name":"Free parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Free street parking","enabled":true},{"name":"Parking","enabled":false},{"name":"Valet parking","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"B V","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLs8DIWqrJjHu-8KrgUtlm6SoXr8DrEt3snMCTOHJbkPdWiKQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dining at The Herbfarm is truly an experience, not just a meal. It’s a 5-hour, 10-course tasting journey, thoughtfully paced and beautifully executed from start to finish.\n\nWe experienced both the vegan and non-vegan menus, and both followed the seasonal theme Solace of Winter. The menu changes with the seasons, which makes the entire experience feel intentional and deeply connected to the time of year. The vegan courses were comforting, creative, and surprisingly indulgent, while the non-vegan dishes were equally refined, layered, and beautifully presented.\n\nEvery detail stood out — from the stunning presentation to the personalized name cards at the table, which made the evening feel extra special. We chose the alcohol pairing, and fair warning — it’s generous, so be prepared for a hangover 😅 The non-alcoholic beverage pairing was also excellent and paired beautifully with the dishes, making it a great alternative.\n\nWith most ingredients sourced from their own farm, this is a dining experience that’s absolutely worth the wait and perfect for a special occasion. Highly recommend.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0ENiIMyARnIGsDgW0VQyExZ7ypouJnElQNtTsq2cuoflfEj_rxnID1IZiiIdYIabrph6GZGQXL1sdDmUjK0vZ-Z0OurfJh9bsIWBEZSA1FKWPHPyhUCUPHCMcqIM5KDryYUelDSmj6WsY=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2GqZThroFIkxU1ueV6LNCJQJoTYym