they put something on their fries to make you keep eating them ... And then there's the beer.  And! He atmosphere . Ahhhh!!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn28tRwfwDspNRZcYO5dcdpq77U4p0gP0g4KaG-9vYZ6TvQzn6snewZHoOsHyocCBqAlJE9Ud05dwMb34I33sd8CK8CKTQpznx6EQyebb82lc9UR9qlqzfAVtFeLIdJssY_Wzy8mpoZKxe8=k-no"],"When":"2025-10-31"},{"Name":"Dale Burks","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVXsGPY0qBpOYtyOjEEVsTgs7tHJiJdoVkRMXqPXF0lpleRBO8a=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow, we walked out and my partner said these words on a phone call, “We just had the best burger I’ve ever had.” Well that’s like a national holiday popping up on your calendar. That’s like the perfect summer day biking or boating, type burger.\n\nSo let’s clarify - those french fries! They kept getting better with each bite. I mean, you’re full, and you can’t stop eating the fries.\n\nTo make them more range-y, they offer all sorts of delicious dipping sauces. The chipotle and the garlic were spot on. Did I mention that fries kept getting better? They really did. I’m good with taking the snobbiest of french fry lovers the Bison.\n\nBack to the Bison Burger, cooked medium - it was perfectly medium! Thank you. Not the - well, we overcooked it a smidge, sorry medium. Dang that burger rocked. I think time stopped because after a moment my burger was gone.\n\nIt was only a 20 mile ride so I’m not sure why I devoured that burger, but it was great to eat.\n\nThere was a nice Fremont Pilsner and a delicious cider to help things down.\n\nCool atmosphere - soccer and Mariners everywhere. The place was bustling at 7:30 which is nice to see. And the service was excellent.\n\nCan’t wait to go back and try other items on the menu.\n\nThanks Bison!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2OG7nR3DOOmy-cNy80wihCSP-VLJKAyAKOXx3RuVCCCnjydvLX6Fzeglp2K4zlLBoCRuf7lsZpJXDgoo8GJnRru8o4gh3lZVVXqyXWcxhin3LCRTgNmn6Eo4sn11gyb4S7yP89=k-no","http