Iapyw4e3H1FFhPxum-hvJY04ZOhdq2ZcTqhp5sPYePY5gKXALzok8mUc90ElwEZfQxVJB4ui8vUEs=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0rsy7RdpjcHfMaBIpeOhoEwqB9BOnD_Osma8AlDEvP-p0EGQOWfwLhYzk3Fx9pLLByA-h92NXytKq806TRUVl51-7VMcN3NBIc5T76hUHLyT7MN6RA_6Nimw7hYo3fH-5YJa6CaP7I0OGT=k-no"],"When":"2025-8-15"},{"Name":"Alex V","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXT6QdP0DiTayV8QMFhY3I_KTMooyAcw96Ncy_kCImEQMRTjO9Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We’ve been here twice for dinner now and both times we were left wondering why this restaurant wasn’t packed. It’s a family-owned Indian restaurant with delicious food and genuinely kind service!\n\nThe garlic naan is some of the best we’ve had—soft, buttery, and packed with flavor. And the coconut chicken curry is absolutely incredible. Rich, creamy, perfectly spiced, and savory chicken —comfort food at its finest.\n\nIt’s been pretty empty during both our visits, which is such a shame because this spot truly deserves more love. If you’re in the area, skip the chains and support this local gem. You won’t regret it!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2HjcoqwqZYsaz-sznzPotJ_ukl7HaQCMdxTvpQGPE3dYgnhrhoz2qCotNOirB2v7ZTvpfk80ORV-Dw7s92xkJg0B9vt5taHS2X15rFURbjq3VX2uOUQdxfpQjLKyCSbbQF8o9EBA=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0aDL_4GTtA6ud2LQF7_RMZzFSAkqtrOmBahfC9tBCQnKVJC_pjJbjwStdpB3eC-4qRHxY-FkHdGS25zUV7opJEZBOQ_gs5EngzHWSVQXPMsoTrbiuF8qIt5dRp5Y1t_FN3XQG-=k-no"],"When":"2025-4-4"},{"Name":"Kathirazhagan Appavoo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWF7fGF0cklevAm5r46-sI0pMcGStp0ipG5De7MZIO4_uETNNqAjA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Went in around 6ish on a Friday evening. The staff were very friendly and courteous. They did keep checking on us (probably she must be the manager or the owner is my wild guess). Ambience was also good.\nThese are the items which we ordered -\nPaneer Tikka Appetizer - good\nChilli Paneer - very good\nGyro Platter - very good (loved the meat texture and softness)\nKARAHI (GOAT) - very good\nGarlic Naan - good\nChai - good, felt great after getting wet in the rain\nKulfi - good\nThey do serve alcohol as well.\nI would definitely recommend this place and would visit once again later. Parking is a pain if you are totally new to this location. It would either be street parking or the parking in the garage behind (all spaces were marked resident parking, so I am not sure which one is reserved for the restaurant). You can probably park in the town hall parking across the restaurant.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3o5kXACZtQQJE3L4lsDTyUWVEIAHmkG_wMLVUs9SicNkaflyInBJfBgxQv0l2NOnRKSwORj_yppv9TkV3q-6XSt1Iym_gv_aHf5T-iky6t7vonfOoPK4RGqyXpGI6dpaMyMJbX=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0XggAbH2hooatfw3C2sch9oh5RDn4fEeFN7cMLWBxEZCFrJ-hJMl6cSkh_dzVZxeWxtBTaynivoG1IIO7iOgaUYS38EqawXYg4TyxvULEZPeG4edLvta4x5FfC1747KxdIAE1bpg=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2PdDWYOyTAx8kD1ZNOuCZjSoDSPg2LuFiL2vhDzbLVFNDC5PDwuEF7i6jb550boYjEWBsbCBGkwvFkJo3Q3aEGobQvcrHcKqCOQpLnvPBncsgw0sr0UNn4z3CroVVVH_SWd7Y=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn04WRmMamQ1KOg5l0-JqFXVuxWDa-cpgkBfoeOSxy0Cf_YqMEllI-J34-NyAg1FckCAAGIZwXc9Qg-UA3w-JFKkZjgseAVy220U_LwOpg9moh_EmhDyfLlIAsHIRjbVXbkF0It-QQ=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn04GXv-g2eyhpsnV4GeiVsyRWPhBIj7WoO0nd_5QLV62o7rpAEmiy_1iEMVM5UGHOPz0bCqVwucUlS06PySGGkqQifiZYXZe8awOC8M9ZbDrdNrf6ePBdhI0yXoSzxkJ3UeOZ3f=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2FyQa7l6WkGU8zNasTpdGm0B8iyD7XINZlBRHYRzwuLq1LTlompeY6bAJi8_zZUYJsc_l252733FU8QM9C4J9BBlsM_0vemkUEAQmgqZgQ-x05EKPbjA7g8UrtPGUQ5vLZqzIEcA=k-no"],"When":"2025-3-24"},{"Name":"Anastasia Zl","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUBe-AxSQeQUwERhY9MyWjSaDtJH1rdaq38cG_JlGi7tCrJhFlyqQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice Indian flavors, a