tor of the absinthe cocktail but my drinking friends (I was designated driver) chose the barbie cocktail.\n\nWe started with the crab and corn hush puppies which were tasty and a good appetizer to share. I had the tomahawk pork chop which was excellent with plenty of vegetables. The birthday girl had the king salmon which was cooked perfectly and tasted excellent on a bed of flageolet (\"flatulence\") beans and mushrooms. Our other friend had the clams with chorizo which were spicy. Everyone enjoyed their food.\n\nWe finished with the pie in a jar (?) which was undercooked but edible and an apple bread pudding with caramel which was pretty good. Our friend's dessert included a birthday candle which was brought, unprompted, by the restaurant and is appreciated.\n\nVery buzzy atmosphere, a decent menu and friendly staff made this an enjoyable evening and somewhere I'd happily return.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1KVUcxGzdRDs9R_hAtBwfLkDPufF2DIB12fiK9agNqGV4EcSIcLu2kE8AJUUp-1yZWvGhMDUeWbNPdtluAx1gRnppSs3AR_jsV-XysMbYWvKVA3BoIwZGckbBRig4OajMgLv1TUL1PncKV=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2HaadJZkL_nUumL1EeuVmbo3a-vv9hciI9uw0J9TFZbGdRqLVd6KsHKR7ywXi02I1DpPqTKqebl-5KmVawSXqwZgub8uz6dEahrdTkXaZJfxzOtdL_NfGDuQLUx-JdIZWYtiUK2NZttHNB=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0mrn3GFJDt7G4457J36y4Uml8wKdauVAr6aBq_L0_3PW382Ka8nTXBSy38otnuQVE3K1AqdWB3-4hhC2JScc83e3b7CkvpcAIjX9TPGNK1zGc2BErSS6fioG6PhDUo7c-hUw6x_-m2MZ7J=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1vBbgVPgBus_RlmZEygRAnj4XzU5aw6BzrVXXaHY2cCHwJS133IpkA0R1tOTPSPiKy7GCZHHqUg8IJq2PfksH-8lxlMHGbKNJB044rf4INp7tNu5ym4nVBLTnAihtxSvFna-21_1YVf_ER=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1xoFMKj1REWV7Wi7KgNAAEJ73pq3TULtLebls6TvyBZGNZQzqw1LGGok0fQ2o5rNmHo5oveC4cACw5UTSVsEHJWeLKlbDuJK7U3SWMgbBc2Smn3JfjntKR8zsAJl7ciEL2zBnt0sEDltbU=k-no"],"When":"2025-10-19"},{"Name":"Halley Bylin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLR_xVeuPv4j478zYtKE8z1r52wflYPTWCC65YSONwC8CMT4A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had an amazing dining experience at Heritage. Truly recommend them from a casual dinner to celebrating a special birthday. Of course, we had to order their famous hush puppies. We ordered the 12 ounce steak frites. For dessert, we had the ice cream special and pot of key lime that was amazing. The service was impeccable and even the ladies bathroom was a lovely experience.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1Khkg9zRqVDIVbUghU8cUQUCoOvfLmnM7M2uNmOF_EO5TxX_FtN3KoHJsOC-m9ctieprKhrajq6LrX0jGxSb51Apv_hBuPX-GVOwHAh6bfRWWcKC0xFJQ2dq9IX7MM2qZ6LsqtNfdqiGvW=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1qDfO7RcNitnr1piAj8wMTijMt6naF9jMrGbLr6TM_nN3V6JiB-hBH_Wct4TgjLdWaZAreN1J52x-0xWvv6mUwwqJiT0QSbpETL1jNWMIaYm5V-CxqhyRXBA6Qzntf_7eQKghk3NmassUM=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0K2TgXMBnsSYRpDAqHXb0eweYg4DgQod53PZk_lqKzJS9F6TZFLOPCbvS4BWMKSPj2-S36rKEawSVctqgWQ1x5HeoZOH4EZB15CmJ2AX0ZkQgAUjNinfE2F-Q_o2-luAcOG1_p5Pi_-9SG=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2p0YXwhZWZrEJdprUupS1tXW7h23lFNEEuJSVgwV7Ho7Xu1aK6yLNm5f_esa__WmP2VRzIipYlq27AEoWGyi0X8cjGh2VO1wvnh5AAeRZPXJbCOXUiI3bsgb4DxiCr8eqJ7QlkbpoaZ7Ey=k-no"],"When":"2026-1-14"},{"Name":"Kenneth ROMERO","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLwWG1A8y1rTbMq3aRfWv6Rm7UfGb5NxrLLOR_Cr0u6yw1J2w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Went for lunch today (1/27) and we had the worst Ruben sandwich we ever had!! Bread was greasy and burnt around the edges, and corn beef was fatty. We ate 1/4 of the sandwich. Fries were good but that’s it.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1cBcLu7wJ-AM6tFB4xvQ8JMbkEtrMJ6j592GJGBzxJUaamfRoTaB7pWsZnNg3gNnCwGaZ3UEaaKz__3Nh4FsYhuTDSS-GdIYU_zY4pjLHWgvZvablbdWJ1tfFIQAT6FAEz2S7Nw02iS3cM=k-no"],"When":"2026-1-28"},{"Name":"Greg Logan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWqMPdkhkSa6c6sXb67RoskJh3OoIJNXqGxk56EnAXZVzBHF7yJ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Update upon Owner Response\nYou follow-up is a positive - shows real care for the business.  Fair enough that we could have at least referenced my primary complaint re portion of fish - though not sure how to have handled the bland sauce for the salmon.  Your servers have always been great.\n\nOriginal Review\nI have been to Heritage 3 times.  I typically enjoy myself - the staff has been good to very good - including Eric the manager.\n\nHOWEVER, I have become somewhat disappointed by the food - including the portions.\n\nSpecifically the last \"fish and chips\" for $30 - well, the tartar was great, the fries good - BUT merely two pieces of modest sized fish???  for $30??  Come on!!  That is ridiculous - toss on a 3rd piece of decent sized - NOT over-fried pieces.\n\nThe king salmon for $43 - okay, sort of a normal price in Seattle (with outliers) - but expecting a bit more of a portion - AND a sauce that actually had flavor - instead of the completely flavorless sauce provided.\n\nSo despite having enjoyed the bartender and his custom Paper Plane, etc. - and the ambiance at the bar (much \"cozier\" than the front room), I doubt I will be back anytime soon - there are just too many good options to review.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Devin Mennenga","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqG3vuebXxA4TZElqECeaqc2_woTwoQXRyaZX8rI6RmHohlKvZ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Heritage in Woodinville is a gem. The food and drinks were both outstanding. Everything was fresh, flavorful, and thoughtfully prepared. Great atmosphere and friendly service made the experience even better. Highly recommend.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1YkaNmUr_N01zvId2v_JMhIxYADFGgw9PxedNergHhW1N3KNBhGZlfsotMx1ZtQ8tZ-8UMSY3xOh2i5MmC_vAF2UORQHl37nmpgiH24JcRjToQ20uLDcVP1zTIvICU1TOV85sJ6fbAJLXo=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn25rt16LWISQfN4SIF3yRfpO--jCLd1mXaMHZUgpPNnzOCuCeVPeo7TfAMej5zpCAgU1olGUB0mQAVpEDlSxnFChI1si7HVhVrcHjMoX6e3XJWO1x_LwIvy0QyBN6L-cOFivO3UZYdvBken=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3BQXGzkj8YWh1uNB9DXW_INUj94GJHMhu7R-xEUOFIvDUab53F6UErxq3FthPX3ED3QIM8eXV0cJEtiJ0vLRMpcrpg-G46u964Kgbhaw9SY7CwjMnnSnxzY0v6uRG_-oLkqHnr-D2MecKx=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2OhaYhiqrStLJIyY-8IVejEDb-jKnXvgH9oFltKdr-I2M3qxBPAVJrfPcLZDBdRWY16FlxhfuvrNsaCI7TQEdaq5Lex7IhMjaOof2qRhZPSBPFqxNhdF794DiY-lzm_oJQbOp5ZCZy6IP5=k-no"],"When":"2025-7-19"},{"Name":"Christal Griffin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJNOifNJspivp-CYg8GTW9TmQXS1PyfJZ5ftOZ7BcCU27jRvA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Love the location and ambiance — that’s what keeps bringing us back. Unfortunately, on our fourth visit, the food quality and overall experience fell well short of expectations.\n\nWe ordered the brie appetizer, which arrived cold in the center. When it was “remade,” it appeared to be the same piece of brie, simply cut open and repositioned with jam added on top. It was still cold and congealed when served again.\n\nThe salad portion was also surprisingly small, especially compared to nearby restaurants like The Shed across the street. To add to the frustration, I sampled a beer before ordering a full glass and was charged $8 for the sample — something that was neither communicated nor expected.\n\nTaken together — repeated service mistakes, declining food quality, and unexpected charges — the experience was disappointing. Given the price point, it’s hard to recommend, and unfortunately, we won’t be returning.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
