uWFYtZT2PoSMt7dtjwtyRB7MWoyaasedso7eKiAt1uNeta=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1xr1KTkZyzCH4w0nmdJ1yu0Z5fPdzbBrxCoxAgpNw9OUXhnFcefDFh1iOez73j_1wH-UsbZ7qPuUfmcVLVOgaZHieUjr77KUZYijUs0YYbXLCEgi5Z83Ea_ctSYUWnhH_IJIYNIvRtoN3W=k-no"],"When":"2025-11-4"},{"Name":"Scott Hancher","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU8yP9hoXq9kYjWP2eo63Ahh-8brL1I4mySpuj5HWVTm0gtElA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"After losing our favorite Mexican restaurant, El Toreador, in Redmond, I stumbled onto this modest sized restaurant with exterior covered seating in Bothell. I immediately knew we were onto something when we noticed one of the El Toreador 3 brothers also dining there with his wife. My Chicken Mole was delicious, the sweetest Mole I’ve eaten. The chips were perfectly warmed and loved the accompanying salsa. My wife’s shrimp tacos were stuffed and very tasty. We’ll be back.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0zNvdxtXMC3XI85LngkV-ZFbGdQJQaSK7t4RZ4BuY2NF4U6O-mlgjmL3sRq_A2NMaYLnWQD1SNdht0HDcYm1g1ar4h-cgtVV-aRsrP7K0enfw_yKHTl4G1YYdBcpDRmpTghONa0D-_UHvJ=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0m1La8OdQOl3hQIxUmrrHmtCE9vrAzk45NUlEo23dEYeROpeqDWIW8wU6nF19mBtjqcXRhf-vBZt6A8FP253f3ySq0Wcz6xzRdQVjmPJWfuEtls23xkGLCEt8vNSL17TwmxABo2_rt29lM=k-no"],"When":"2025-8-25"},{"Name":"mindsushi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLTD7Gzh_OzpxUVilVVnc3uz6hqgLm6O9Et3nbN3p3uGfqhHJE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Chips and salsa were free + Portion size was very fair for $14.\n\nTastes good.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2q-Bmzrj2RWmSfKoUI7yNcN0096ssqJlCN2sxYomrXvLJwNTzgEvq-6kvKkHVgINc9pKWEaD1pgL2I9nzN2K7i3pNxdivsNrQktWO01PMmN3XZvRUl8EqOVS8fIT5iV0NftKExgMPuEuLR=k-no"],"When":"2025-10-6"},{"Name":"keerthana natarajan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXjp5jH61h2RRYcsFHw86PqBO7s6cYF4ej_vGc7XA7rdVGwjh-H=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The waitress was very rude and angry. They served just plain white sticky rice instead of Mexican rice. When asked she said they serve world's best rice and mocking at us . The chicken was bone dry and rubbery like a real piece of rubber. The hot sauce given tasted stale and old. Would not recommend if you want to really eat true Mexican","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kevin M. Pennington","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU2-hXSTEgvmnp6awIzx3AHZw_sQ_HK6KzHAU5x7wU4QHE4ji3s=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently visited this cozy and welcoming Mexican restaurant and had a fantastic experience. The atmosphere was comfortable, with friendly staff who made us feel right at home. The food was delicious, with authentic flavors and generous portions. From the freshly made salsa to the flavorful main dishes, everything was spot on. If you’re looking for a great spot to enjoy tasty Mexican food in a relaxed setting, I highly recommend checking this place out!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0EG2Brh3tF7c6Nhf94Ti-80MIPHV5jDTSAEL4tyIXYFOMsvWkb33yKc_IaP8I33vBBZn9ZcJxB62oRp5Rx5mc1tyZtzWfJ8e5q6eYovrWuq4Ahp3b5vC7RY_zSplqfBr5n2NPr=k-no"],"When":"2024-10-8"},{"Name":"Heidi Hamil","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIsBtwAqlYPoLaDhu_cizXutEm9rHEOX0xChlBQtrrkRPD43g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The chile pasilla is the best thing I've ever tasted. The homemade red sauce they put on it is divine. Chips and salsa are great too. I always recommend this place. It's a gem.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
