","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Brian Young","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWAy39xHQxgd-DMD4g6ij_iceUV785qFafG_f_928FEHk6Y_Mk8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went almost every Tuesday for tacos.  Service always great.  Go a little early or make reservation because it will get full.  Parking rough because of construction by pier.  TVs for watching the game.  Outside good seating in summer, can’t beat the views of Seattle and Mt Rainier.   Fish and chips and clam chowder worth a stop.  We love this place.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Catharine Parise","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWTfqgAI-uiCJK5H0Qazz9WYGr1UuE61aUoH_RdxGgyZKzIL4JeWw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Peaceful outdoor seating with beautiful water view. A perfect place to go with family and friends in summer weekends.\nThe restaurant's menu has some classic local options with seafood. It was the first time we had crab cakes and it was terrific. My husband had the fish and chips which was crisp, fresh and crunch. I ordered a salmon with rice and veggies and it was pretty good. My parents ordered the Coconut Shrimp as entree and they love it.\nThe service, specially the waitress, was super friendly and patient. The ambience is casual and relaxed.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1q9ttl9MdBG16BoFo4pWaFeoYkfRM4U3LN-DiuiJXfOpKWU2mxRt3B1_kKIUprJVwXslXqDy5439yYt3qZOV1mlAyy3comxC6ScBCev8dzEqkUHUHQ23o43eq7FjoeHtaOEO1V=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1Cn8U0Gg3jwknpu1kdwRF65UVNqrce9LNNyosODyo7BDG6UdQIq6jM9LpHsrNUG7g_X0XY93rjoF9upHxDETJN9BsrSWiGGyWf7pUOR5rKuna0S2qg_AAadD7NDXEKnk00etcjNQ=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1224pIkRbo7UB3d_JvywD_l8Rqy3tRnG6btgnXgj6nwSSb5PpVCYxewN4NwCK-wuROo9F-xC4FPLv66APnSJXziHpYHfyCyQb1cqadj8G2yNjOBu1RVLcncdGwEwJZASCJrZDR=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3SbJi76mOwPFYhyNlUbL1TmU9-kXc3Rv