fUVt2tIwr1p7FpXxITDtjx0NcxJnsd1g=k-no"],"When":"2025-11-15"},{"Name":"Scabbers Adonys","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWgorAxwR3TsNosgvMqeWC1o2cLhD6xYissnPQYeZ-vL6jRvhkH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Higher end seafood restaurant and setup for groups and dates.\n\nThe Manila clams were great, albeit smaller than the   New England style I am used to.  They came with butter and were a great appetizer.\n\nRustic bread and butter for the table was enjoyable and better than most.  I loved the thicker crust.\n\nThe planked Silver Salmon with Red Pepper Beurre was outstanding.  My only desire was the fish was on the reasonable but smaller side.  It came with mashed potatoes which were also great.  The vegetable side was mediocre.  There was nothing wrong with them, but I think Brussels sprouts should be cooked in either bacon fat or garlic butter.\n\nOur server Timothy was knowledgeable and friendly.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2xKnszdnNePPPz14Tcm0ZbyhztO0px-nJ2XD6p5KTISYley7He0VwbARNpcErL3ZfkyAwleSSA-87HMwipu5Y99uTaVzf-sAMayRyjvhl62c5opefkIQEwTJM3azovMg4_RWvqUvviwbhq=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1PhP5y15XoNS1M-sHWvSccOE8H52iGqrHP6Ez-i4DBoAvuwIQU7LIubLK-15ykiOyjeHcqmfDPCCfvidJorx8N9Imxl90oHolHZLKW31djc_n7dk4SICjRmzXlqti44aNVbSdcTRyOk50=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3KFkUcuMGIJEkaVqha87bGFd-Q9ZsFuo-FkEmkfMqVXujrjviPqkJMAN_CZW1aBNzjSkcKiLrKSZ1TQcoJCbQkBtSUGxljERvEfdxAd-cTv7Zz6AqcSY9cFDuF4dIPfj8qlw_p_NofizY=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3x3PF0sMy16IXOpNdPNLj6hVe1lQRklv4L46Ulw1jzZjzUGODSleWzM845rqPdzCU0HUS0q3snBKIYv8rVZcUCJ3b9NJdt1r6J7rxnaYLjMT6tfZNf4lB9WZ4ZMPcuCeH7u_KsnRw74-mi=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1iPzQJP4kckXqa3tivML6uLA3H2jEulNzBSeIgVgW5TC0ZpNGHCP4Dl39qWGnYBfS5iu81HPZyOheHxtAMFvcloAMk5EAQbilvBuzRlgOovdy9mR9o_Cf0ZfNVs0blXrpp9tS7rmkJbB-O=k-no"],"When":"2025-9-28"},{"Name":"Patrick Teh (Licensed Tourist Guide)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWhX5Fe21iEoRWVf3s5zS2bk0khG7bguMWVryz2k0mPbeJyphLzpA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Just happened to stop by for a snack and a beer.\nHad a clam chowder and a nice local draft beer. Clam chowder was disappointing. Too dilute for me.\nBeer taste so well. So fresh. So refreshing. Coming from Asia. It's really appreciative of the quality of this beer.\nClam chowder small size is too small for me. Taste so good and regretted ordering a small portion.\n\nService excellent. Was served by a lady with the whole hair done with breading done by herself. She done it wonderfully. Again, we don't see this in Asia that much. She is friendly and helpful. Appreciate her service.\nAnd just found out that She is starting to collect foreign currency as visitor like me strat giving her some small notes from our country.\nGave her a Malaysian Note.\nPass it on.....","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2WwtUreeu6JqzZrVHPDVHhp8qNXkMtZUfyumcomrXpD6VSNzBUhG_AAwNBa1rMCC4mtcj-iOL1rWmMqPWQ2QcQLGF6uuU9wuNBDLXYAmz5oFkEb7f_yGNEDWQ-3_dU-QFePicFa45SGwJy=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2RFMT-lK3MT5YQq85TlGjhZW-3SEN_501eX6Eeh6K2KZ4h9BJbKjKXDVQKYo67fDisxnezpXILc8TDOYtJYATf4mM1FoxpKNUYSBZz32pooARjusplkv3VLJFYczWpPfYJ3aKQfsB34gPa=k-no"],"When":"2026-1-20"},{"Name":"Kristina Wild","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUf211swyeQPl2oyYqYE0MBNY-DFilHcW5YB06DDWIs6wBD500L=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Really amazing day after doing the best self tour ever at USS Turner Joy but Derek who was our tour told us about this restaurant and we decided to try it. It was good food","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0LpUPGeHsP5WY5a_JN2eL7NkEhObdGQuFPWWv1h3a4WpzyR173MspQiXK-yVwv6DTejlss4vRBRPQgs7vKaknUYfuO0WYXIQoHwCjDQIplHrSRKsKljstnf565pqNvX5gpPaS3Zqs0h6VI=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn38v9p0nqUwUUXvgAgsg5uAg8s1m7U9p90pcVwYY6CRda1X28tu89EeOwZEt15BNOVN1JluS6V6nWVinfD2ii8oJjhqskRkuMglqV42EeLrem_tT286Ya5ssX5vWSUpFidIwhVTtvvWTJzz=k-no"],"When":"2026-2-6"},{"Name":"D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLlKCsI9_Cv9wPYq2XkTnW8GL6EXFF_gDCQfDk3LrHE3RwI7Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We planned to eat here for dinner but ate so many snacks but still came. Our server was happy to serve us a 3-course meal to share and gave a great dessert recommendation.\n\nHostess was a little confused when we did not have reservations with an empty restaurant but still sat us immediately. Maybe during busier hours reservations are recommended","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dawn D'Alessandro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV1NTSmTFKjsUFNBKcGEfAo1rv7erMiz1WxWKlHGXNBnXgneF0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Waiter was attentive and accommodating, food was great, I had the fettuccine with salmon. My husband had the Salmon both were delicious. The 3 course option meals are the best way to go if your on a budget it gives you the starter, meal and a dessert for around $35 pp. Most meals on the menu start out in the high $20 range so it's a great deal. The restaurant is clean and with great views of the water from almost every seat. Parking is validated at their parking garage. It's my go to for birthday/anniversary celebrations or when company comes in from out of town.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
