B2e5IpR74qmo0K7SQKAEtAUd94OIo7SujWLGEXlfOs433zQWgdQG_Ez2-CJEOzIpQ9E5jzm1uSognMHfm0XVFikKNHZ0YRLl0Ily9oosEhGWA4qmBncCYFR9l0lyHDFIo=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1lSja-OdKLs8Tkcz6Ol4LdVnU6smO9Ey9uoEh98rckA5MyaNXryJ-QNkJ4kRvUS405EiNWj7e7Kp-cV7h9pGAuxFieNxdXiGbxlBRBDzWzrvGRPliHvAfN7jUM6RXABZs8gBmnng-KZHP-=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2OfCOmvbHg8nrAc6Aay5fyGFSBCGRfpeFhn9AKoLYolX6ptScv8-Hl51-kFRb9_SlDBg-3YrLdyXAxXtRKurJkbbJyxIlGj9aqL3OandWraZ5TZc93_2lSqYePKPLiCVcuz7hMRqakd8r3=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2hkXoKeLqwAexKxoNoEw79hgLxgOtK2HQ3yZG2PG38i8muFae1s_SzFuwQqhHdib4LocQEGCOSSN3Ck8kL1eE7eHWT_Wy2m6xXn-WIRUvic0A0jthdo9worwTqVCtFBgJ4jsvFw_GWme7D=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1RryNcQzVs9FtgAZYsaX-bw2fU5NsB4MoPQvGE9yQ2o4Mce9TDj_lOWX9DIAy3Ah_i2ji6LYfoObdsEErkpnCNqAJvnj9VkawoZqZwR6yv_DYTHVVrSham2fbwyDnkce32c76RcNirJGis=k-no"],"When":"2025-9-8"},{"Name":"Maui World Travelers","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUXU8BK10V3s0a1GFHIRwzDSJwst7HOKlwRTO2q5HMMIr_iNM4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Friends of ours recommended this place. I do appreciate them, really.\n\nATMOSPHERE:\nLocated in the Miners Landing mall. It's a huge restaurant with indoor and enclosed outdoor seating. The only view is from the outdoor-like seating of the service sidewalk, and a moored ship bobbing up and down in its slip.\n\nFOOD:\nSourdough Bread\nThe standard free stuff. Came to the table hot, crunchy \u0026 chewy. Delicious!\n\nAlaskan Combo\nKing, dungeness, and snow crab legs, head-on shrimp, clams, mussels, andouille sausage, corn on the cob and red potatoes steamed with a very mild salt flavor and paprika. The crabs were good, but the king tasted the best. The clams were super tiny and tasted okay. The shrimp and andouille sausages had no flavor. We're not a fan of mussels so they went uneaten (and you can't substitute.) The corn was good and there were way too many potatoes. Comes with warm butter for dipping. They have a minimum of 2 orders for all combos.\n\nThe bucket of food gets dumped onto your table then the bucket is placed on the floor for your trash. You're given a wooden board, mallet, and bib to engage in your mission.\n\nSERVICE:\nWe walked in without a reservation but got seated immediately. Our male server was friendly and pretty attentive.\n\nOVERALL:\nI'm coming to the realization that I'm over the table-dumping messiness, table-pounding, and sub-par seafood accompaniments like andouille sausage, mussels, and potatoes, in order to get my seafood fix on. From now on, it'll be strictly crab on a plate, and a shell cracker. Thank you.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3uk4aEJGIX33zlYOPpfxNQs7-y8dW3vtKevf5k_XvS8DgLkidH_Qs4vQ21rrRY0OQ27s5taaiB2g09lablgcPZepZfH662YenqLh95IVZk7rWKNuhNYwkEHGOPTfP6HTPlvpVNwoECtDJQ=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1B4xBxYZ9hjyrHMgUnlLK_pvXRfyiyWjLSlEPHitscicHsXIQ2kDkhISHg2b-GMzsvGlo77tORhDsUTxHOUffgHJeuu2FFIqQjdQSJlHYCL2-VH36kt-sRRV8O1dbIvKIrB_OMO9FDFcFP=k-no"],"When":"2025-10-21"},{"Name":"Crystal Knight","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVVWzAQj7lodeWl2Yum9sx2-PnwRxQv6giNJw9OOTUpLv4wL-f3Nw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This restaurant has been on my Seattle \"bucket list\" of things I wanted to do before I move this summer.\nThe service was beyond amazing!  Very friendly and right there with drink refills and such.\nIt's a very cute restaurant.\nNow let's get to the food.\nWe ordered the Sea Feast for 2, the special that was on the table tent.\nThe food is presented in a fun and classic seafood boil, pouring the food directly on a sheet of paper on the table,  they give you a wood board and a little wood malet (crab wacker) and let you go at it. It was super fun!\nI want to give the food a higher review,  as the seasoning was lovely,  the potatoes,  corn and andouille sausage were all cooked perfectly,  this is where the issue lays, because the seafood is cooked at the same time,  this overcooked the crab and lobster as they have different cook times.\nIt was a bit expensive and after tip the check was over $200 for2 people. I still say it was money well spent and a lovely place for us to celebrate the purchase of our new house.\nOur server was super sweet and I would consider going back just because of her.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Vincent Campbell","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocII2ARux3Prns1T8rIX52RoK1R2DBug5gQhW7Or18HNs1iMWA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came here on Valentines Day with my wife for the 1st time and it was worth it. The waiting period to dine was only 45 mins but it was no problem, they will take down your phone number and text you when your table is ready so we killed time exploring other stuff around the area. The restaurant is located inside the building which can be easy to miss due to other establishments literally around the building on the outside. We did the seafeast for 2 and ordered the Alaskan combo which was $89 per person, we waited for maybe 20 mins and when our food arrived they literally dumped the bowl of seafood on the table in front of us which we didn't expect so it was hilarious lol. The food was good, and it was a big portion for us both. The con we have for this is that they do not do to go boxes for the seafood due to them not having the right containers to properly secure the seafood without it leaking the juices from it. So hopefully they can invest in something like that in the future. You will have to finish everything right there so select wisely, but they will have to go boxes for other foods like pastas, burgers, fries, etc.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1Yd3c7NUgPN-fukA0-TIottgankUvl1fbgJlKTg8eby-u2WtM8TJNzluN_8XmFH8za4-3lbePX8bWDfdytg_JtECIknrnj1-HWVs03HLVUt-RmNrw6wl59Ur1qkVhC5UhIfZRmhSgCks0=k-no"],"When":"2026-2-16"},{"Name":"Trade Links","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU5MA51XhcOXjvUsjCWgiSl0eLwqTg-gwljXZG9O6Gc3Uo8kBtP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A super cool spot right  on the waterfront. We came in for a late lunch and ordered the fish and chips and a fish sandwich - both were delicious.\nOur waiter was fantastic and provided excellent table service throughout the visit. The tables were spaced out nicely, so it didn’t feel crowded and we had plenty of room to relax. I also liked the ledge by the window-it was perfect for setting down a bag or sweater. Overall, a really enjoyable experience.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Marsha","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUMoOk8Es5_nYyw2qW-BZvfKzCQ5IVSknRAJR_2X-4HNhO0Bx5D_A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What a fun place and what an amazing meal!  A bit pricey but ultimately worth it.  Great tasting, fresh seafood.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2h-hw3wpoNV4yt2MK2-n0FmO7UeFn5qmrUuMp_z27xia-tpi7Eemcj1GzFP6FZ2vKf3lQuZxK3GPfBcYfuom3djwyyWn622H7G5rEJb-sJkM_DMhmaRqSkl7nXvCR5KQvwHpk8pyCK99M=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2HWWv2tH_Bqa9hzSOJEFLUlB60DERrAESeqXEllOuAhCb_G3t_LOOPw_5-b92lg1wPqH4bSK4G2qvSC9u-HYsTXTERsIBQDNbHdKybs9Q0zt7C5ErEaoWDwQ-sXD7Y9wQiVJcv25ilmVvt=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0RrwY3Fpg368pRXBSS_AVCmYCnpaAsWY4Yk8l6MC6eOkki0KhkpgRCZGb9SJaLwq4_QSSnm_FAIu4ePZF4u51hty7hMW_zpbWYDEdwcn1JJpaNlWGKwk_jQP4YQwWmY9J7mEUgWtK7IOJg=k-no"],"When":"2026-3-10"}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
