uld strongly discourage anybody from going to the axe and arrow.  It deserves 0 stars.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2NDWXfU2tbp-ljALtCTfi8LU2p3YGqd_DdN36Xo8k8unPxzBuLgGfOmeFD9iPQ7kjABWXkiTon5LKdM_BFVyuluJHFVL4wAjuFF-lYWHlnC2cU6b7YfogVp6vJx8CzZ54bICb1FmbjQYRN=k-no"],"When":"2026-3-8"},{"Name":"Megan Andrews","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVklE9VtPy7jfq-dV40Uw3f-FeTNqnbldXXlaRRdm0Stm8sB_FtYw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Loved the location being walking distance near our hotel and Roxy Theatre. Overall, three star rating is based on food. Coconut shrimp were the best of the things we ordered. Delicious. And brown honey cake for dessert was good. But the ahi on the chop chop salad had tough consistency and the prime rib that we ordered medium rare first came out well done, then second try at it came out medium and was chewy. Bottle of red wine we ordered came out of the bottle bone chilling cold! It is definitely a great spot for whiskey lovers but not so much for wine! I would probably recommend trying burgers and sandwiches. Watching those come out of kitchen looked really good.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0sR6i9h7HGDZ6b2_L37G8FIPQE2fdVedXgPeD7uFcQ5gT41zdDEimlF15qHExVKaap2YvwESxXn0ZSQxv4asPV5Axa9Vp2oilLQN94qmpivUvMSMG7qfUB75qJEaCdcEfX6StdSnxT38bL=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2SHFRqoH5guMe4moji0kiTBKnXtzF-zbspPm23URkhM8_r-nACmnlr8_tYPcdxByRdDAD5VNOzppngr-rTcRB2QvuaEwx_ebhFN6D1l91HyPshhw8z0aQLZs7nZMVBYF0CPdSefieQOVyH=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2ivIH1pFX_iGffMD8OeaS-9RkIDbxJerQtvujmis4sToFK1pxn02ZDkLj6900rzR0xNtQUy2AayouSyHrrwVlZ1s0WR0pE6Y9xVcO9doWdBSfIlo1nwgDvVjCH7gfjR24xths4zFj9H0Q=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3XTtBMoYeOH2hBrRkT5bs6PPv-YXPIHwEU_o4dVwuTnznKwGdV5qHmUs56u3yBCzi0FvCEEjWlVHU7g1k0fiqhf3izy2hlQM4VVy4wIpHYm-wVPYvqxzRHJUa9E0mepw_guBmNoIpcbrDm=k-no","https://lh3.goog