ood value, especially compared to other restaurants in the area.\n\nI had the Ark burger and reuben sandwich. The Ark burger is a simple, well-made classic American burger for a fair price. Similar burgers nearby cost significantly more.\n\nI appreciate a proper reuben sandwich, so I'm just glad it's on the menu. The staff must have PTSD from people ordering the reuben, that actually want pastrami and swiss. At least, I got hit with multiple questions confirming I did want the thousand island, sauerkraut, and horseradish lol. It was delicious.\n\nSeating area is somewhat small with fairly packed seating but is kept clean. Bathroom available, also clean. It has hot water.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"waves7","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVjmYxxhZnRKHJDaSq8ttKaN1JXOAf-a9ep3kAKBjABfd2Rrag=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Noah's Ark is a super classic family restaurant that is trapped in time but in a good way. The interior is super classic without feeling dated or unkempt, and feels more cozy and retro. And despite the name, I didn't feel like the restaurant was overly religious or anything either. The food is pretty good, and they have a very wide menu. The price of everything was a little high, but not incredibly unreasonable. I do wish they would offer more combos instead of selling fries and drinks separately. I would definitely recommend this place to just about everyone stopping by the area.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kristina","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW22-RUEpRz_Bsc0-qn7pGRG1XeWEPEfCvZpnktyJrBkMH-U5o=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very good fries, crispy outside and fluffy inside, I also enjoyed the burger\n\nAlso good shake too","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1IJQnnNDYVfXA-VVlRX2d2ROQDTxCegEjtQuXT3-f793HVUs_4kbv3OmoNNarR1d4gsj31ySsoJTpokE3ahTs8LSpn0LluepUO0ZiaFA_H5os1IJV86Cf25EC5S-TPAmVxhXBZVbvgSjb7=k-no"],"When":"2026-1-7"},{"Name":"Angela Marie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVnAUSrYgG4iFIg_363_vLyQosQckQUEL7oFAfObd6acDSoBwY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We decided to give this little spot a try after reading some reviews. The food was okay, but our Reuben and Pastrami sandwiches were unfortunately a bit soggy and dripping. It was pretty busy when we were there, but the staff were still nice and helpful.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Penny Huberman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIK0fak0cUCQdyqt3d1lJaRYwfVJnsIDnwXjVmJ9JBtDIEJJg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"So glad we stopped here. Its adorable and the food was so yummy. The charbroiled chicken sandwich was phenomenal, my partner had the bell pepper Philly which was also very delicious. Would definitely recommend. Oh and the milkshakes .. um .. YES PLEASE! Give them a go.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
