e ambience is pure cozy nostalgia. It feels like a place where time slows down a little, conversations linger, and breakfast actually feels special. No rush, no trend-chasing, just consistently great food and a vibe that makes you want to come back again and again.\n\nSome places are good. This place is part of my life.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn32p_4JMmrAJTZIUnglh6KpDfbevmzU7xn6CIMmSm7PEQe105BYOiajnVBHe-qSUxq8jSzsM-GwX_FcEKpU9OdVofPI-phZiNurCYM8tyQEdgqB8NTydsXzZ0kydqzsKXHAQe4CEmf-fbAL=k-no"],"When":"2026-1-3"},{"Name":"Chris D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJieXbREH3UDC1pyoB1Eju6LSFrWYf7DItEf6Q2qZn9N1R8ww=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"How does a Cafe serving ginormous prices at fair prices stay in business these days?  Maltby Cafe should be on the Food Network.  This restaurant served the largest salmon benedict I've ever had in my life and it was 50% the price you'd get in Hawaii.  The flavor was perfect.  I came with a party of 5 and Sarah was one of those servers who could make a failed dish no big deal because she's so nice.  My entire family loved the food, the incredible value, and the service Sarah provided.  I apologize for not writing this sooner.  We had brunch on Oct 11th.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn11jSZsAKCdFtpo2YmbZ9r5Lxo2OWSjhxjj-x8i-dzFya8-jAU3zY3jj1yuwWvdZeWRC34qZ6XoYIhj7aZcH5_aqT89s-WXP1yvBC3okeiETdRjyPvPxZl1LS4Pxj9ADgDC1zMFemmIg5sV=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0JPFEckhgnhjTtcjaTu-cWQnoyPTFPvzZAkW6c2z9ul7ZdRYdD_LANrgAAe2O5rjKyB4AeURDIXO3QB_5ra0jfdO9E3TLolriSq8h23jKd8jahL4HVBhn8r01pjVJVrj43HQkwxVy98Nbj=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1KeiYHakNFoSKfzR8mjBT-ntcStTGh8fea1bDiPpFYI316kJs5zEsJFeEWuc5t_ed7Z4iXf0HbZmy6mg4W0iScIQrmKJbM_PbmFusySA3XNiwfJElX5JgUDGjNzPFUwBFtQuJliAU7I7Qe=k-no"],"When":"2025-11-11"},{"Name":"David Forman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXvN3LkWKheqJrxSNj198kI2Eu8Lf6Cj95LVOlYvYtqg6kHvCxfnw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's been a long while since I've been to Maltby Cafe and I'm happy to report that nothing has changed. It's still giving you massive amounts of fresh, delicious food for a very reasonable price which is a rarity these days. Couple this with fast, friendly service, great coffee, and a great atmosphere and Maltby Cafe is still the best breakfast in Snohomish County and maybe even Western Washington.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2t2aM5_R1usix8G05EhEJ5KmttoCQjLHRuVB7vaEBjDchw2YKt5cyxdpx7oz9H9lBtYUwIIEioG-Yzm8Ij6tGtfa31jMpk27k-nEbQ2Myuf8dGsMfRpg1FKkwW0Z98RvpeZSqma_gTxGo=k-no"],"When":"2026-1-19"},{"Name":"Alex DeMartino","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWZL9hCL4qQaKAp6KEz1ZOnbsMUy4q-S2_JDOauWzLnCkW-ySA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We got the Popeye omelette and a cinnamon roll. If you come here, you need to get the cinnamon roll this thing is huge and tasty. The omelette was very good, the filling is a good mix of savory and salty with the sweetness  coming from the eggs. The side of potatoes is well seasoned and don't need anything (ketchup or hot sauce tired them both). The cinnamon roll has too much icing and raisins whuch are my only complaints about it.\nThe interesting part about this place is that it is in the basement of the building.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn16Jgh8HffznAdHQxdbhmDTAHPes0bGA4hxfMPU0n6-zJIXyjtiFEchdq5VjbQmOVpLXxv_IQLSIXz6x967FylhJ6-LmPIBinnQb98P4-1u-l4urjhxhGEzVW2ePUkB35Asg78s9DrGt_i_=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0G04KXDxVsLZFF5b4tL-0W8AyrcaFkBtYK-c7jOwcp0iHOnTt189gRqlCxCLtRBfRYrOaCcq_Ebgg9wRoPOAffR_RkJjDdxlp1tsoNb3npv0uIfs4m8aGv_dtNzdLUzpF3ab7j4yPIQQQ=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1jxUMMxp39M5Jf0NZU0W90tyMYoankMzwKwHaTovVsQSkSWXpyTQBzwE_nEGE8KU7FvinvnLSLyS06RZWELQBRbvyuCfF1o4