//lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0umf-L0CpCdI5HdJIOh2Ahr36jTc9zzyUidYby6oFq1renhS8veZkJIGNC7jPzbfbqYjyHE4_vRGP3Li9ESh9b0S6B8Y9oF9bnkHgBCRbKAMDe4OYa7r46Ty89OBQp9Ybm9wKSR5Ds8Dt9=k-no"],"When":"2025-11-9"},{"Name":"Anastasia Zl","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUBe-AxSQeQUwERhY9MyWjSaDtJH1rdaq38cG_JlGi7tCrJhFlyqQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"There are plenty of outdoor tables, but few are equipped with heaters. We enjoyed live music and were fortunate to secure a table indoors, as it was extremely cold outside. I selected this restaurant specifically for its cioppino, which I had been craving. My children opted for burgers, which turned out to be excellent. The ambiance was pleasant, and our waitress was friendly. The food was decent—though not exceptional, possibly due to my high expectations. For wine enthusiasts, this place might be a hit (we didn't sample any, but it was clear that it was popular among the other patrons).","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3SQ8DZmCb9MxiMZBjAROUb-WD1ELuYZaVjnOZKR7Dq386GlNkt5xXeEGSz09xsVHzxDd13GDeC10KT5qt-8-hgODsQjH56KiHbCaw0jLytshCJUqBfY5vLD0xnlPiAFYPcFdq9nw=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2GD2sxFqC3Ip8NU3peXvrUw-7dgTumBLTXdUFfl95bAtoA-A80aohdOmIL9nwkl9vXFQWtYmrs0zBTtt4jFpRydGgwJrHiQ-SDp7INfPR18aKXHEAtqgS_tOH9D-pEPOlvwYs=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1KZGK5u67v6E7jE_cVst4BTdZI6L2yH3QLtuxSMgJpVDyzysWXn9rl_b32nBvteDCimgaMlt9K_EgG2PruQ5nAGL3NT3gWYYbPT84D3y0OdW50R7EoNfedN6QVn2QPv_S7LIXb=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2ADxUlhEYcs6P2Y-pJGCELJ82u3HsxKDUz-3Hz81BtqArexVmgNSwiNDuQeWzu14bac4AR7ROmb0O5KX3QhseCeXVTUKEhAd7bZdzKu-ecs6t4endZdGgSV_ZkxMLRo-AOqOU=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2aKN5T357z2LrZej4BuWWRl0IjuYVgcmFrMyEztBCBQEKU7oBaV-n6A8P8jE1wbXnVkenYRQ_zgFlkSsTeUylIYD5vjY--CBv-JdWZMgUAXiZVOlOJ1qteNlqyi0CGiWd7y9bAEA=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3bvwemApqUI4JQBu8I0lOgQ7HUnZ0BI_Fnhe_Sn-KdjpAhnNnRIHC3Y10ks4WC7MzYmNcgK6b3C0CDko-kPJuAh1I7spawmPtX0kcyWsaBRad44GdSqG0jDO0nfCYoK6s10KYF=k-no"],"When":"2024-3-9"},{"Name":"marvin wood","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ9Ge6uTAc0RhSdDi6L2laW8tCZtWKxhqNGr1gueulv8geQAA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Would like to thank Sam and Baruk for a great evening last night, we all enjoyed the food and the whole experience. They and their staff make the whole evening a great experience. Just want to thank them so very much. Marvin Wood","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"B S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVEiTjwwK1cgUUD5IkP7QrzE_ozo4Xj-ByqGA4G6gd6pG5jW8Oi=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"7-29-17 update: Posting a few more photos. Still an amazing place. We love coming here. Always great food and friendly service. The  bread/butter plate ($3) has potential, but only if they changed the bread. It is not amazing. The \"butter balls\" and heavily-garlic-ed olive oil (amazing!) they serve with the bread are great, but the bread itself is a let down. Check out Tandem Wine Bar (other side of the valley, 4 minutes away) if you're a fan of fresh/warm/chewy bread 😀👍 Anyway, The Bistro always has great specials, perfectly prepared sandwiches, great fish and chips, and juicy burgers. It's at least a monthly stop for us.\n\nGreat sandwiches, cheese platters, salads, deserts and WINE. Not a huge selection of wines, but there's no point in that. This bistro is bookended by two fantastic winemakers (J. Bookwalter, Market Vineyards, and Amavi Winery), not to mention the other two dozen wineries that are within a short distance, so come here after tasting elsewhere (or before). Or, come here for lunch or dinner and enjoy what they do have on their condensed wine menu (all the wines they have by the glass are very, very good). Outside seating is half of their seating area, so bring a blanket if it's going to be a cool evening (there's only two fire pits for ~15 tables). They will bring your food to the other 20-25 tables that cover the three adjacent wineries, so you will not be hungry no matter where you sit. Enjoy!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1wN1sWKn4jjpqIbOnPn2OYJ5pGtDbesbf2uviUNnMdEgyUV4-Y7Ud2NZuTvbBoCEpROloJAHZMIXGXHkGctKP-B371teeNe93JZDTP5aE8QQStDyDAGFcbtMCNKDXBFBnSti5s=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn34IEeAML-Ugq4xuJ6TU2asRCJwRUbtisE7wzTRv9mbB8PCpxEeJQHFRrDn11XUgSfnZtBC9AckqwaY1a6q6H4HnBMPHbBh8bylSocHLUxTOKqaFQmWsXmnGcss7-yVej1W0HrY=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3TVcqRElOYu_9nGK73ICrqfhv5knBzMWPzejpwGAAZqzW3df41vXmjdaUSKUb_XUKPWtWPE1lP0VUXdr6E7wSJURsJz8VSrSJLJtFCEpd61qlaUmSTXBNAnXOyM_KjrQxuM6M=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1acxIGKM24TyB3Re0zsTP4JunQ8-SNTXT0uEok9aeaRXmJiPcOtpidfBjkm8gLEytCVfZrUKd3RVEKaa6az0YG1-1ANKfAPj_WD4qXsmMB24ywhzlo26MyhDG3NWmlOpcIa27Q=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0uCIXHcxrNFJqW7lQParHpqYIC3anZA_0ZIG-r-9BrLOb7_DgdH0anZh9Ct6dk5Wjb1UcA-EzgjRmZ5qO8SZ3Fitelf9slgNvqZahFOi0WpiCFv0De4-st4KdIEcg-bdJ4ICWf=k-no"],"When":"2017-3-19"}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
