/grass-cs/ANxoTn3847QvQY8B-YksMLSOICDkQl2XnxzZngGHxUtSQXVIpXg2jgYqa2K_z7tFce8stij6YyZEQkq__0MKRgBNB79dKN5idQxW51FcsyJkkvKOCi9IK_h5HMgnEgrtXxHtDvnXign45DO8gu23=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3IRsendcGMl9MIRzaqKL4Jb220Ynm9iM9uXDK4DRfyCY_g0RViFLJK5arRpaZiGM3LKEa9QYDftX1zqDcOSH7fpsa9KOSG-fEZBf4TrSO-Yzpb2GjdKiqIIkOGhPWbMAREXKlhZv9Vq38=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2KxdixDlJp47t1tL8C_FQvArlIm5j6HrZZyHc_dcPN105M7nL03usykuFRrJTqZXV3fBy1ArmAZ_2Td07zYNj78YkVbMMv-fysTGYJDjviYEqH9AbNROe0BV5x0dONhsBNped3K3dJf59a=k-no"],"When":"2025-12-12"},{"Name":"C M F","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKiFz-dQ0IuVdval9ydybLDQjFO6M2yclmzNcTwx-Sk4zGNTg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely loved this place. The food was outstanding—fresh, flavorful, and clearly made with care. Every dish we tried was perfectly balanced and beautifully presented. The service was attentive and genuinely friendly without feeling rushed, which made the experience even better. On top of that, the ambiance was cozy and inviting, making it a great spot for both a casual meal and a special night out. Easily one of the best Chinese restaurants I’ve been to. Highly recommend!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1CKSrWR7cPd1R4DgXXUAXCuq3bvsSTGZnBsjMvgn0Kdpxq-iXrjV9rsOwDKMm4BdDkFUsg1PZyIe51t1X4PwcIXbMBgubRTgjEcZfqZafoXz90p88Cn8Nup7xm1Pe8TdZ1Pgu4nTeWIuZh=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3FcC1coVHRObvsM1LTizT83YBHo7SoGJ3AF70g7TCP4mAC983xbJMTZeygVByMEQU0-WQ4s7DqBcYEEQClNQKUOQZlF6cWIBT5GYu3-r4qN04a3Ub_-zQdb1SmyhBs6uGIw5p_THKdwQw=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2sOKNrv8s9pKF-1mHCPlnjds79_OdxBsDZsOBEKiLsDiyswlsHkjfAi-_fURUdvraGbcVHSuyLcDPD8guKp6kLyyLpsK9vGdFv_eycqcPvIgsDf5YUhOXL-LZup_FLIRaN9Q0mOvk07cE7=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1kt3T0PkG48FJ5Vml816NQL4YpIT_3vEhMR3p5CNQnbO9dygtVWSZgdT9c0zcUlF6vMwHePQmd5Y9nS15b9hUtNo-0MYCWJGNa1PQD0eMs9fezjvtJKwUMLJy22qXDdla0huZLS26V8LUG=k-no"],"When":"2026-2-8"},{"Name":"Jeff Smith","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK5PwWLK38beFY07tK-zgichmhC0t63nvQSzy4drn3aizXetQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We recently had dinner at The Spring Bistro in Bothell, and it was absolutely fantastic! From the moment we arrived, the service was incredibly kind, friendly, and attentive. The food came out quickly, beautifully presented, and every dish was fresh and full of flavor.\nThe portions are generous — we’re happily taking home enough leftovers to enjoy another great meal tomorrow. We tried several dishes, but a few stood out as clear favorites: the Pineapple Shrimp Balls were unique and delicious, the Kung Pao chicken lettuce wraps had just the right kick, the lettuce wraps were crisp and flavorful, and the Dan Dan noodles were perfectly seasoned and satisfying.\nEverything about our experience was top-notch — quality ingredients, great service, and an inviting atmosphere. We’ll definitely be back soon!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3tty4gDmro7r7iCPjFYZR-i5TnxZNIO-wgQG7ZQbsi9O_xclmESmOXN7XIEQG6o9ynW8zVjeUde2zDcUh_uycCIqE1XJIeXXe8QHzb8nF3xZzjmJtCwItkSqdk_jxkRANkCadNRdEfVUaV=k-no"],"When":"2026-2-27"},{"Name":"Lee In Kirkland","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWkJo1jKV7XSXdY4NDsfC1wxR-hCOXW2ovKJC1rdA3c3zU79Sg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is the 4th time we eat here. We like the place a great deal. A limited menu with carefully planned offerings beats a wide menu of poorly prepare dishes any day.\n\nA few notes of the dishes we've tried:\nThe Plum Tomatoes with clearly well planned flavors.\nThe fish blossom, a dish traditionally not prepared with tilapia. This place did it with tilapia, and almost pulled it off to his the inherent unfavorable flavor of tilapia. You'll find it if careful\nEat this last if you get this dish. Its strong flavors likely overwhelm other dishes.\nThe cumin beef is well done. Tender beef with just the right level of spices. Strong and flavorful. Equally good is their farmers pork.\nThe pork ribs is also very good, a nice spin on the traditional sweet and sour pork ribs. Good balance of flavors without being over powered by the sweet and sour or salt.\n\nAlso tried their beef and lobster pasta today. A solid entry catering to the more Western pallets. Lobster is impressively prepared, avoided the common pitfalls. The beef is done with salt and pepper with mushrooms and onions. A little bland, especially if you had the fish blossom on the same meal. The pasta is buttery and soft.\n\nAvoid the shumai at this place. Shumai in name only and disappointing in every way. Fails standard shumai of both northern and southern styles, both in wrapping and stuffing.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn27JT5K1tkOswH7Huoul6SXD_3LLLVTBNr4sw0UJdyo8fkO4LmIgNXuiJQd8PBKd_VrF5pLcsvy654rQfMq5n129r_kv55y7LWn3y5dU334apcZpO0Fo1umBZPLHbOBxJh-iZ3GL4t9ctc2=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3rTPewxGIZQGj_cWq1nzSxUShsZzil2LdQ3BuAg7OE5ju5mrGrMQwh850WxMWQfZ2wdPYJbz35ga4YMEoorsSLuM-ZQz98IwHxQLAM5t2Kwhm-4U0AKg7II0nYRObZ_lzB_SbWnA5VDI8=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn316tRjMWHq5PmpQfcNewYWrnJU9F6puL8axeVdXk08mjsHSOJ9Hafm5fdryWDOtSXaGW04Xf4_h0BhJyo9m7fdTEi_GMgr8u2DZGHQkIpwf37w2_foQY1D8Ivc8b5n6XbktMZIONgrUVBt=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2hh9H3KtyHa8PLvR0EWqWxHUJaChCSI3AJGBs1nhWX3KhgI8a80YHt21-odIeKkqKdI7dIx3Gy3hXAs7Y7-kxqEmcVbNxkPd6XHFo8Xani4JFwr5giaWo2ozlUD-HDZ_Fyjf_V38pMziTC=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3ktdxcL_pr-8nZRrmRK3HhKgquzyq_I9gqTgOLcFvmrJGpgqTcUcRvMU5FLQlkQ1nBaiRZ8zBANrU-GjTYdrT1RPnUpAllGWdqi8ipRo-lnjBRAZpKPVFuAp-uS5aw_S6H_unaHy9ow-c=k-no"],"When":"2025-12-13"},{"Name":"Jessica Wan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWB50zU9cVFVVAAurU45VCeDtXgBzKWN17t4tC485SuA3mxmCqDlw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We went to Bothell for some businesses,  found this fancy restaurant nearby we are very hungry at 2pm, order the recommended  Beef cube on sizzling iron plate and Dan Dan noodle, the portion is big enough for 2 hungry adults and thus I have not ordered additional dish, will come back! They were opened in Aug 2025, beautiful view in Sunny days. A great bar for your drink.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2znTJ-5BdnnzSihRV9gdR-q6HAAK6ja_0GS8T9_ToeAWNtRUZkimMfwhcAoB0jwzYPhwjWE0QB67nG8H9xi93U-J7RB9DwMw8ryDd5SrGKsHHKKvBItoYGvPuiCUIwAry8urUnC7Av--4A=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2Fyqcvoh_cOH1Jknoixkay3t_gGtIzyCE5wFuUNJ6KWe1aG8naltIyYXY3_Foami3DFZE5YSiafy4So4F_ayIY0J6snTSPPsmBQJpfKra7Ef1qH44XL4JYfHq6UKoE_UcoWlpcZHpfAO0=k-no"],"When":"2026-3-10"},{"Name":"David Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLrEIyjZ6oHsa36kI8TKlRRR0jv1VkAjzlV5spmrro5nq1ihg-i=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great Chinese food in the downtown Bothell area! The interior was well decorated and the windows beautifully let the sunlight in. My favorite dish I had was the hot \u0026 spicy wings.\n\nThe hot \u0026 spicy wings had a strong flavor but were not overly spicy. The meat was juicy and well crisped. The garlic bok choy and chow mein were also solid. The xiao long bao was just okay. I tried the beef and lobster pasta special and the lobster and it was great to try! The lobster was pretty good and went well with the pasta sauce!\n\nThere is street parking and also retail parking in the building.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0tqpzXw1FJ7lWnwOhAdVAioqo7mIgHFhrzQeWbOwrFuXp2IjRzAbI2UxaCBM4MebyRRzgMQwF_oE0GMmeFEnP_tMDiE0idGK0e3HyrG6a0lPCu27yR1Ocooaf-4cN3O8_fDzvd3CHHTFu1=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3hqimiHHucYKgNrkobuABxFXwuz1vW9qGF_5-V7YKs8m0bY1v6C5JRL7fRoeXKypM0qD8RYFXQ17-grKp7BQhnueXPO7b4drHun-hSX