 waiting. The shrimp appetizer was seriously good – we ended up ordering a second batch! Portions were decent for the price. A little quiet at first, but got livelier later. Would have been nice to have a few more comfy chairs.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Indigo Wolf","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVM425w5SZ_kYwGMVpsORC76AlGKUrdMoKx67xwcZTuXhFEUo9X=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My friends took me out for my birthday and I got to pick the restaurant. I wanted to go somewhere where none of us had been and looked around I didn't want to get some place too expensive so we ended up going to The Filling Station because it looked like kind of a fun place.\nThere was nobody in there just some people finishing their lunch and then we were the only ones.\nYou could sit around the fireplace and eat your meal so we sat as close to it as we could. We sat at the table that had high chairs and it was comfortable. They also have booths if you like to sit in a booth.\nMy one friend had a wrap with I believe it was Caesar dressing, another friend had a burger and I had the French dip it was so good it was piping hot even waiting 5 minutes it was still hot. Usually when you get food serve to you it's hot but then it gets cold right away or it's warm not this food it stayed hot for quite a while, at least 15 minutes.. but all the food was good it was fresh and I certainly recommended it to others. I would definitely go there again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Erik Oppenneer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKLlJ2T_cCX3j66Q57JLxsP2_bjOLYPABZCdMksS8bW0TJFow=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Met a friend coming off the ferry, first time here, the staff was friendly and attentive, the bacon wrapped shrimp appetizer was awesome, we liked then so much, we ordered another. We also ordered two entrees, fish 'n chips, and shrimp basket. Was a quiet place until Monday trivia night started a