king lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Free street parking","enabled":true},{"name":"Parking","enabled":false}]},{"id":"pets","name":"Pets","options":[{"name":"Dogs allowed","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"sarah ragland","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKza8ihRvYZCWeBrOdaWhhC3qI5wLXlbDMki7qRsTlD4_7DzQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I visited a bar/restaurant in Bremerton, Washington and immediately felt out of place as a Black woman. At first, I didn’t mind because I was just there to order food. However, I sat at the bar and had three different waitresses look directly at me and walk right past me like I wasn’t even there.\n\nEventually one waitress asked what I wanted to drink. I told her I actually wanted to order food. She said “ok,” turned around, and started doing something else without taking my order. The service made me feel completely ignored.\n\nWhen my food finally came, the potatoes skin was left out of my order and everything was burnt. I spent $77 on food that was practically inedible.\n\nI did speak with the manager, and she was very nice and tried to fix the situation, which I appreciate. But by that point the experience had already been ruined.\n\nThis was a type of treatment I’m not used to dealing with, and it felt very uncomfortable. If you’re visiting the Bremerton, Washington area, just be aware of the experience I had here, especially if you are African American.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn35TriWQIMwhAoh_7SnqMEDaaPVlq8HqWrPWqu3etlCO-DpZQ-fB9ZIYL-sK1aJXzUIFMkjZbYhOMQiVbVJUQaP4wu8-_34R8JxZ46Y9odxGoeelkISAmDYaOucuIw7q3j9_q_if2lb4Tgg=k-no"],"When":"2026-3-7"},{"Name":"Chris Sriracha Vilhalla","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXwFc_Zzqm_4UvORApOiQBx3IJE_i_NpQa5AAaYnJqWpf7oe6rX=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"My server was on it. I unfortunately did not get her name but she didn't a wonderful job with a table of 13 people