eel completely at home. Definitely worth a visit if you’re looking for a relaxed spot with great value.\n\nWe’ll definitely be back on Friday — they have Music Bingo from 6–9 PM and we’re excited to check it out!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jennifer Quillin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWT3cbzo9K69tN8dojikd28nXZr77SUA6BQzbOhvljQlKcwJ3IQ_g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What a gem! I love local pubs where you can chill, watch sports, and still hear each other during a conversation. Steak night was fabulous. And I can't wait to go back for the broasted chicken! Fun and fantastic service is the icing on the cake.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0kBdbQvi9iJkkFthI5LJMBSuJy8zgycDCmJIeL7FxFhsbpfwZviBaB74CFuA_nLpzYjfeVV8MRIw0MqOHJ8SnNHr9XaHvNe9r6Pqai5K5-gRUJUD9gGuzG_7vYydMWIheJwHJZ=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2OsW--oN79RreZxzge6vnFZ_YobAqCMg2xWLexEppflWkVn8uIae4gv7uz1-qE3yeFPUiDWVJhK9QyzZgQVcLBqxCIOhqpwKUBLLl8wN6XN8WFXntT1PF153DwdkknW0S_0GvPoQ=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1LNRQ-PPaBkRhrs5mftGYsiYHvmsvxyeGP8iHJIHrji917g6N9aXklcFlW-Y1NTwpGN1IUDvYrurUqa_-H8bJGU4Loy8zaEJpuvDWgUwaROdz19iF8olI-uaz1TBJFWNcKgcVz=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0_n_FOhJTOM0r5it_9PTaXQmBq3Knuj5bxPUERnDChp_PVZ-eVqA1KEvE4Q5VDRKGoJ3ZvJLPfBspR9wq7HFgLmYiWDY7tdb_7ihdMAhNvllKkV3rbbHFUzxoRi8nzXIs3z2er=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2XLFPGnS8l_odAi-aDvB5ncm_ADTKIanKZ82lV1qPzHtzOsK5vTdkA8-1ygup6Iu8hL8awGka1LsgZos5RMkxhNmitgV4IWX5rQ4KXPpj02NAfLHE_ajwhl1eXyK2ZVRjTUNjQ=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0tnPmjiPk0Y8uqpfiGavrQt7kxl1TQfcF8jmA-FWEJvI1DgKze2E-ISWWkjXAgjGroBGGU6i_G4g1G8o0wlvOLfTQiuOjZ_iGBVq3TxdXmuvgcf89OnAUDVWz66jhPtla42NT3sA=k-no"],"When":"2024-9-3"},{"Name":"Michelle Peterson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV3nY9TwtF-z-JsmH9ONLHG4l-si92CIAGBGIr1yOJP8FaydjU=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The room was beautiful. Nice interior, super comfy leather chairs for everyone.\nGreat service.\nSean was our bartender and was fabulous!\nAll our guests talked about how great the food was, and Scott was a pleasure to work with. Super friendly and helpful!\n100% recommend and will celebrate here again:)","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn02OKOxhVz1Itxcn_tZctDD3t6MGaAze2nYy0gXIlJi41I5HcojRFmRpU0KnnP0TjZmdKsB0HYTwtyPpqGmVEXKPh4-bWCIREMZM_rVWbCusoNCC31eJXiL9RGj7ScUp7wLArM=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2WH-JyvzzYGF-gZKMWBCP3zJgchlJMxyE8j5dttjbXdkUuErCGeyXvsv7Zxm9HfPNucLoIk9igp96IfUW4dOSkyyLC4Fxr4U1FGAMofTbEZaRbsdGnxSi1SB9xckNdzJLmw3CW8A=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1q_JBxNbkY7r0tPJJfCzvcE2Ajnfcd74tm1_B9JIEaylHDy7EL07626yuTMgWXaArleUubWjykwCen0jluBcUyIPKIw3e1JjkxACAcVJVWWv4oqE6qRxKrmO4XhdzjS2oRFvi5=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0RSve7toL0ewTveS2ZRfDKnNknU9JXMiIwRDOwbKXwBStvPmhMo9GtImcKnP6SDoXi5TBcK-JgzqMSb2-p0dtaf_1ylKs91uP8AdYo8zkJJX8HihnL2lcjSmelZz4_pNZ2Yxboxw=k-no"],"When":"2023-2-4"},{"Name":"Christine B.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjULWaXV5XRTuCCZoXB7XFzd5ugyx5gMDJF88VrhoHyHUJugy4jz=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"UPDATE - 6/20/23\nA few days ago, the family talked me into meeting them and some mutual friends at the 19th Hole again.\nGoing allowed me to try something else; this time, a Taco Salad was on my radar.\nOf course, I had a choice of ground beef, chicken, or pulled pork; I ordered no sour cream and chicken as my protein.\nThe salad was lovely visually, with fresh Romain, onions, tomatoes, cheese, olives, two salsas, and topped with tortilla strips.\nIt was a nice size, everything appeared fresh, and the chicken, although mixed in reasonably well, seemed shredded and seasoned. I have encountered unseasoned meat on my taco salad, not with the 19th Hole, but with one or two other restaurants, and I am not a fan; at that point, you might as well call it a salad!\nThat said, overall the salad was tasty, fresh, decent size, and seasoned meat -yay-\nAlso, for an extra cost, you can have roasted jalapenos, guacamole, or avocado added.\n\nThis visit was busy and extremely loud, last visit not so much; so come knowing there's always that possibility 😉\n\n----------------\nFirst, I had a hard time determining if I should rank this a three or four-star; three and a half probably would have sufficed had I had the option to do so due to how long it took us to get food. I opted for a four-star because, overall I felt they were better than a three-star.\n\nYesterday, February 17, 2023, hubby and I joined some of my family and a friend at the 19th Hole for lunch.\nFor anyone unfamiliar with the 19th Hole, it's a bar and grill and one of the oldest, dating back to 1939.\n\nCruising the menu, I decided to have the Thai Lettuce Wraps, and hubby had three pieces of cod fish and chips.\nAlthough other family members had food, club sandwich, another thing of fish and chips, and clam chowder that was also ordered, I did not taste their food; therefore, I will only be writing this review on the Thai Lettuce Wraps and the Three piece fish and chips.\n\nFirst, the Thai Lettuce Wraps. There was plenty of food, and the flavors stood out. As I have had issues with other restaurants, filling the lettuce pieces with the Thai mixture took a lot of work, so I chopped the lettuce up and ate it like a salad! My only tiny quibble, a personal preference, is that it was a little bit on the salty side, again, my personal preference.\nAlso, I had a small piece of my hubby's fish, which was a bit on the greasier side but had good flavor.\n\nMy hubby obviously had the Cod fish and chips, coleslaw, and french fries. He agreed with me about the fish, which was a little greasier, but the taste was there, and the fries were typical french fries, nothing fancy, but not unpleasant in taste; the coleslaw was pretty decent tasting for restaurant coleslaw.\nThe only grumble I had was it took some time to receive our food.\n\nOur server was friendly and periodically checked on us, but not to the point it would be considered a nuisance.\nI do wish, however, that she split our checks as I had requested, but overall I thought she was a good, friendly server.\n\nOne fun thing that the 19th Hole offers their customers, aside from their main menu and breakfast menu (Saturday \u0026 Sunday), they also provide Steak night on Sundays and Mondays, Taco Tuesdays, Wings Wednesdays, Fish and Chips Fridays, and a Chico menu which consists of specialty pizzas! I have to mention their full bar, which offers premium liquors, beers, and wines.\n\nThe 19th Hole appeared clean, with no sticky or dirty floors, menus, or tables.\n\nYou can find the 19th Hole at 2171 Erlands Point Rd NW, off Chico Way, Bremerton, Washington. They are next to Kitsap Gold Clubhouse and Events, across from Shell Gas \u0026 mini mart and caddy corner to Hanks Grocery store.\n\nOnce again, this is an incredible way to support a local small business while having some good food and fun times!\n\n*Always remember, be kind to ALL living things.\"","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0m8LlZV0SiRWvJNdfBHav3RKvQeBHm3TkGMXkMfpOfJylWSlif_dfV_5xGkO3BphgKmdWSaZ51-92EjDRbkmmbdHCo65a3svS53FNTYfi7sYkB3tiRlj5mCiiTwQgBQs-MTjHK=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn274dvfiSpUZvJ0H_tFUBFprTqxodxU7XQrFASaycJ0KLigQhcKhvinZ9Hfzn3POKuhaY1CwDhHv6JF3KocL25_oUsLfAWolRMK9i_kdFVwP1hHXR2TIMnIBNa2pEL-TAjXXMf3=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2spm0kV_ut9iGHPhLJyB9RaqbSWwXd6zlj11AIGprMjDbS-9Nt9qjY2ZsJxSp5y7_gR-xLfS-hGOsFQY1wn-5d2ViWnrLunWMVoiQ1JGLLXzFavpx-LTq6iyshKqbEWRqSZdY=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0CUr3vOqU4tAF_mu67d2cZdk62fgfONAvwYwlWJqNTjpUoRKe3m1rjvqgCwVq7dDCmMqUNuTeQca2c6eBQiVXygDsFKTbcamVcsjksMPdD_C7BNuJiUrM_