a M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIFSIoPJE7UTS2UowA2O6t8_XVgGUfIbWVqBFiWWo_13U7zyw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"La Gloria is a Mexican restaurant in Bothell very near 405. It has a sizable bar that shares restaurant space with an Asian restaurant called Inchin’s Bamboo Garden. The receipt calls out both restaurants. I met a friend for an early dinner and ran into a sizeable group of office workers who were there for happy hour. They were loud! I asked if we can move tables, and the server accommodated moving us to a table on the Inchin side of the restaurant, which didn’t appear to be open that day. Phew, it was so much quieter; we didn’t have to yell at each other anymore. Service was smooth and swift. A copy of their menu can be found on their FB page but subject to change. Parking is readily available at the building complex-lot.\n\nThe Food:\nQuesabirra Tacos, $16 – 4 Stars\nThis order includes two tacos, with a side of beef consommé for dipping. Diced onions and salsa round out this dish. The slow cooked shredded beef is very tender and flavorful. The consommé has pieces of beef to fish out. I dipped with the salsa instead. For the ambiance of being in a restaurant, this dish is good. If I only want tacos, there are taco truck options that are just as good at a lower price.\n\nEnchiladas Poblanas with Chicken Tinga, $16 – 4 Stars\nMy friend orders this dish regularly. The enchiladas are topped with a creamy roasted poblano pepper sauce. It is not a spicy dish. Good for those who wants a departure with tomato-based sauce.\n\nThey gifted a refried bean tostada to all diners.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3Uc-kqd8dB4ug4fc5aSVS3EQxV8qeEKbN5KzWZkzVxUgWKACR3Z5i7da1qg7eUGgz5jX2uCxmQ0kd-8_BFu1WQ_ZMN43bCfGmOFpiL887RqIWpN5E3gwlanCzwPu_9l-48FXYhUhBZVgSF=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0xDb9zqjLd8eVIUJTGzvfLksZEAkENTAsWtBUvL3gJK9vJJ7Pid5A2h6PtE5dSqd88mxr5ugAEk0VSmNY96