xidZ6xGkGkgKpryLd_6WBjm21X2r-NsK4MHdwuDUv_zgsWVbstZimZpI6zvNYVGp2ozKQDg-07YrwM7WVHN7FMYptR3k7I9dN73Qq4rCcDtGLxUyzh6ms=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0Iuzb0QMMMmTO-sq076NDk2Nnn_IAYMd1mHzamNHtQ60Gv5-NUGdOqtUcy9UJkQWHBFAKfy_sVRk9uOq5vUSz-DLrZD2B3bDLb6mnMetejFUttULGugiVtA-Sa9i0TBgGQhYIpWB9QTaab=k-no"],"When":"2025-8-19"},{"Name":"Misha Smith","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUSwUSmwu2cSnrwA0ljgHhcrqyMf3PsoK2g64jDNuxrgd8awxNekA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Delicious Food \u0026 Great Service at Rusty Pelican!\n\nWe arrived at Rusty Pelican on a Saturday at 9:30 AM, and luckily, there was no wait for our party of four. I had read great reviews about their coffee cake, so I had to try it! We ordered the sour cream coffee cake, the lemon berry, and the berry coffee cake—each one was absolutely delicious.\n\nI was also offered a raspberry coffee, which I had never heard of before, and I’m so glad I tried it—it was amazing! Unsure about the peppered gravy, I asked for a small sample, and our server was kind enough to bring me one. I ultimately decided to order the Pelican potatoes, which turned out to be the perfect choice since I was already so full from the coffee cake.\n\nThe service was excellent, with staff frequently checking on our water and coffee refills. The restaurant itself is cute and beautifully decorated, creating a warm and welcoming atmosphere. There is parking available across the street and a little further down the complex, which is convenient.\n\nOverall, I had a great experience and would definitely recommend Rusty Pelican to others!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2MWwzi1kzkmwMF3g0nfTYUOHkZdPgCDAH0iM_u7dFyg597_HC5RkAcZvYORu6dRQ883qYhM1woLWZiifykzI8SCCoLINpaCvhRkuDESyZTuk7ssGik9mmCT2F4XczOwDZcVeNReQ=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn21c3oNSkOTett7FRmYxUb_sFqdKKDhbAjOGXcDulnuiy6blSCup1vqbC0ROqZQiKMDXVBG_smy3rVbUBtmlTINhvA7_sl6ww3stG