ass K?!). Nice selection of beers. They usually only have one or two ciders though.\n\nThey do tots instead of fries, which is great with us.\n\nSolid, if slightly over-seasoned clam chowder. It’s good. Good but also over-seasoned tots. Calamari is nicely battered but could have stayed in the frier for another 30 seconds (it was a bit greasy which tells us it needs to be cooked a bit hotter and longer). Wasn’t rubbery though and had good flavor.\n\nCons: Tiny kitchen so you’ll wait a long time for your food. If you’re over 6’5” tall, you’ll need to watch that you don’t crash your brains on the beams.\n\nService: A bit mixed here. Most staff are super friendly but occasionally there’s this one not-so-happy person. Otherwise great!\n\nSlightly off the tourist street so more locals here. It’s surprising though because it and the place upstairs are the only two restaurants on the water with waterfront views.\n\nWe like it and go fairly often, but they need to bring back the REUBEN!!!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1GkpN2mCoQHoNQHQ_s-PvY2XTmKHTp8XlXRUYtdhz0Bbje8RyuLyhHQI-iL5ncOtFem_UNMyndCf_gNSFb36PlA6g0qDwYPr-vz0WUQtQztFkyIhBKW7CtKi0zflSbVhSH4CSS=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3vD8yW1HdYOTYptn4_yYN2Jvek-uYB7MkREHrDG2T5wjeEeyUJwQ7REBKE5DoJhiUBO0ySWGneThymH314LWy3gnOLkD9zO52tA25PPLM38dl-4WyZM5s0PydHQDBRq1U9tBpB=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0OFc1e-CdP7AIx6t5ifVvlu5jkTfzZxau3b23Dc0mOpe5-yn-ONaChxoMCmIRJzX9o79EA-kZ2Dr7uxrBYn4MMxfE3dyFRdO51F12KTMoTF9Jil1NaFr5U5_yZB7btlrFioMFS7A=k-no"],"When":"2025-4-17"}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
