:"Atmosphere","options":[{"name":"Casual","enabled":true},{"name":"Cozy","enabled":true},{"name":"Trendy","enabled":true}]},{"id":"crowd","name":"Crowd","options":[{"name":"College students","enabled":true},{"name":"Family-friendly","enabled":true},{"name":"Groups","enabled":true},{"name":"LGBTQ+ friendly","enabled":true},{"name":"Tourists","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Usually a wait","enabled":true},{"name":"Accepts reservations","enabled":false}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Checks","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]},{"id":"children","name":"Children","options":[{"name":"Good for kids","enabled":true},{"name":"High chairs","enabled":true},{"name":"Kids' menu","enabled":true}]},{"id":"parking","name":"Parking","options":[{"name":"Free parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Free street parking","enabled":true},{"name":"Paid parking lot","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Van Khuu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK8K_H28axKxKznMikfVzlcWyLWeM6liDc3F1eBhXHWOyy3Rw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had a great experience here. Everyone was so nice. I love the Salmon Benedict and the German Pancakes. Highly recommend the Viennes if cinnamon is your thing. I really liked my peppermint mocha as well.\n\nOverall beautiful place with awesome vibes.\n\nMake sure you call ahead to get on the wait list. They are very nice about it.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0AJGZ7o7B_nM7TSD3GKdmpRN29fTZZHi0_GwzNNCq5nB20xj4x51eNe1sVaiOsponrZxZLxNCwfEulnywyCjg_NJw9DScTIz51jE5j-QIHNdQ7l665U8Ig4mkxg433AsJwqWUGf9ggVqc=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0ozkX5k_3GwJ16KkLL--QdlMCYRDRCI1n_BnKGrnM8rPGdqQyqVA37d4PzDTe_jYUMnB7BKYq-2BCrpWINZG1BzC1ek7a0Fe4AlRR6gMY5S8uMwEK0cLMOUpp2XHjiRdboTW-QAeAQVw5e=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0KzKS5bpwZ65uVscOD98kp-_uSrTdqQUSwsnmNn3Ucp8e75zlJQmdnnAjCLTRyIvIcg3pqR-H_339ZM249LvBrPqwOsjNeB9v8329wvy05ysWx1sWjENw8FZBTyzuS0GBvGcR1UE5HGS0=k-no"],"When":"2025-12-21"},{"Name":"Yuki Fujiwara","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUq9OE6pCIZdTJHXqoYmDBsveTbFUdCFL6B3rhWLHFSIlBteoARNw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Trying to a get a table to this place can be hard but going at the right time is the key. We went, looks like after the breakfast crowd but before the brunch crowd. Parking lot is a very good indicator of how busy they are. They don’t take reservations. It’s first come first serve. Line out the door means you might be there a while. Great for 2-4 people, larger groups may need to wait longer. Brunch on a weekday is perfect. No kids as majority of them are in school. Visiting on a weekend it’s always going to pose challenges to get a table.\n\nThe bacon and ham omelet is fluffy and full of flavor. Wife says it’s very close to a French style. At first glance we thought it was bread but it’s airy and flavorful!\nSmashed potatoes were seasoned well and cooked where even if skin on, not too much chew but doesn’t fall apart.\n\nBiscuits and gravy is a gargantuan portion. Their biscuits are huge and you get four of them. I still had to ask for extra gravy so I could smother everything. The taste might throw you off as they add sherry and thyme. It gives more of a savory dairy taste than others who rely on the meat to spice and season. I personally added more pepper (from and grinder, not a shaker) and salt.\n\nEggs are swimming with the butter. Good but could have used a bit more crisping.\n\nBacon pieces are huge. Cooked well, seasoned wonderful! Not chewy but enough crisp so it doesn’t feel overcooked.\n\nI would advise to sit in the main room or a window seat. It’s bright but not loud with the amount of people. There’s acoustic absorption in the raised vaulted angled ceiling. Waiters are attentive, many of them rotating and watching the tables than just one person. Water and coffee topped off all the time! For a first time, I’m happy for all that we got! Will be dining more often.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2uvv5xOTwDDCa4e4Ojqv3aR--iTY_FouyHkRLuu1i6z2con0spbSRF9vtAJKxktQzM9ItoDh6KU1voztAWRpNbe5vwuQGFuxHFM7sf3myQGvET4M2j1RQNHdcrRjxeKPr682p4MmDUjm2i=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1LwqL6dLHSLcmJX4n47U-iOE230hGyEvsEGJeW-5BgGrqe9kSUHbZZci1932O30NouOag6wVmMAdiO0zj8bFyeVf1lu3gEerHX_cchXZtro308Ghiku4hvuq3vhK30ALVEGKCXJKvLbSo=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0YcQ10oMNYsUi2wJ-bFTO5vUITEusle-WrwR7y0QdunagxcwTbZab2-AL9Tun2WT598T8aQ5efT2ujTnU94KcWqeXW70HIyAJNCxrZt6LKdNXxL9fg_SDz9DAOle_WdE5XeZvi8Z3jL34=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2Q48q1s7RDmVZQQje6AxBXTS2D-0lFeZX9Ts9jr5mQLmF3SV09fFyv8WcKg7bfzm6fMZEtfTlA8-KEe0WlKXxTsommYApnI6uL7uFb1-LzdvaimGxPdg2yJMIvzl4vuHO_d1S0KV70ZmaP=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1fEDm27yqYjoUjyf7Z42W_55Fi46egubew2oouLkg85teLk_ri112gdyLwHPwxnlDfkVK099e_X9ztMz-nSXwuvir-zmD1ifNoLlfPzlnZGsdlc0I3bAB4-2qQvJmAKf_c0EX6K0D0rxTe=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3wSAv3cBYZ2ugnk07SbztigqZUFIjVBQjrnuS_aq0HeXkkfXvdvhmBHpkQkwVK8cRiCb9X9OjjYMXEvUCrIZDTD-22g3C7eQo9bTdK8XyOjCGP5sS_Qr9xZJtUjvDjZF7vJxUrU7rIABgZ=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0gc8sq7HnzqcxAAIOpb7Y_O-CWLtuH03_dmIV_peQImrqK2HmH0n0y-Xe9irziy3606QRyVaCrQV1OmleGgjTBodQb8sw5mjeipwucPqfeEerdALmc37wj1Kn5X4R2nK455yHMOapGJV1I=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3LzenGByS3TrGECN9jV6amB1FYDXhyQVqeI05l7ceBIEWHzsSgvJ2c5VvTrIG0na0cCXBvd0-3nf3sxxQLTdiBTJPr8SMkyLWJVdD03qulevMCKUReGKej1_OpiHolfg7tBp4RP5j0mOUN=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2nkNVm2mbhHP3-LhUTdkXpVtEiz_Czy9c0_8eU7zAALO1dTMnq24EuSEjoOD54glnlC6olrL3PZuru-1kVbVT5R6Ck-qetm8t36r2z6evBYUK6ycj8l