hich was great and not overly sweet. Overall really enjoyed the meal and would definitely come back if I’m craving biryani again.\n\nBittu be the best","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ravi Krishna Kunchala","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvjMiwG4_IN3XNAGh_o-NYq-4PwTmaqqsK8BmK21CLG3nsfWGA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Extremely Disappointed – Unhygienic and Negligent!\n\nThis is not the first time I’m facing an issue with Royal Biryani, but it will definitely be the last. I’ve tried to give this place the benefit of the doubt in the past, but their consistent lack of hygiene and complete disregard for customer feedback has left me no choice but to post this.\n\nThe most recent issue: I found hair in my food—again. This is the second time this has happened. I had ordered food yesterday, and to my horror, there was hair in it once more. I immediately called to report the issue. Their response? A careless “we’ll check with the kitchen” and absolutely no follow-up or apology. Completely unprofessional.\n\nPast experience: A while ago, I ordered veg fried rice (our order was one of the last for the day, on a weekday). The rice used was clearly spoiled, but they still served it. I raised a complaint back then too—but never received any kind of response or acknowledgment.\n\nThis shows a serious lack of cleanliness, food safety, and basic customer respect. It’s unacceptable that a food establishment continues to operate with such poor standards and repeated hygiene issues like hair in food.\n\nSave your health and money—avoid Royal Biryani until they fix their kitchen standards and start taking customer concerns seriously.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3Asm4wjhm95HOYflq_GlKdHQnXTdnN8n4nZO3etbHTKypWy9RVLcx61i7G7XrHrXfXTX4-C2C_nqCmBz2ULlEpeplp_5dKdotYfJMT5AaQ5D6UW6Ej9lpxQ0oXqzKiZsLTAq4VLLlljXFd=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1kdDNmqT21KR_fQNyx3VRlgL6ZrKWrnc6q54T6LaXJYto